Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:01:01.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22\b1}片名：不设限通缉
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.82,0:01:57.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈的\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.82,0:01:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,呆在那 哥们\N{\rEng}Hang in there, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:09.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打起精神来 麦克奈利 这只是一场比赛\N{\rEng}Lighten up, McNally. It's only a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.84,0:02:23.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 哥们 信不信由你 你上首发了\N{\rEng}Hey, man, believe it or not abcyou made the starting line-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.43,0:02:24.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没瞎说\N{\rEng}No shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.59,0:02:26.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没啊 安德鲁斯出水痘了\N{\rEng}Yeah, Andrews has the chicken pox.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.60,0:02:28.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你至少在两场比赛里表现都很好\N{\rEng}You're good for two games, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.85,0:02:30.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 那很好\N{\rEng}Well, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:32.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不喜欢 为什么要这么做\N{\rEng}If you don't like it, why do you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.90,0:02:36.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,棒球就是我的生命\N{\rEng}Baseball's my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.23,0:04:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔莫 乔莫 过来\N{\rEng}Jomo. Jomo! Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.23,0:04:46.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过来\N{\rEng}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:47.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 听着 乔莫\N{\rEng}Now, listen, Jomo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:49.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要你把这个带给哈利 好不好\N{\rEng}I want you to take this to Harry, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:52.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带给哈利 快去 带给哈利 把他带给哈利\N{\rEng}Take it to Harry! Come on!abcTake it to Harry! Take it to Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.99,0:04:53.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,走啊 带给哈利\N{\rEng}Go on! Take it to Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.49,0:04:55.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它带给哈利\N{\rEng}Take it to Harry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.08,0:04:58.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去啊 快去 乔莫\N{\rEng}Go on! Go on, Jomo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.23,0:05:20.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔莫 乔莫\N{\rEng}Jomo! Jomo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.94,0:05:22.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快去 快去\N{\rEng}Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下来 下来\N{\rEng}Get down! Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:37.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 走吧\N{\rEng}All right, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.21,0:05:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我还是觉得你该走 - 不 我不能不上班\N{\rEng}- I still think you should go. - No, I can't get off from work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.46,0:05:52.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是你是唯一一个知道那些统计数字的人 我什么都记不住\N{\rEng}But you're the only one that knows all those statistics. I can't remember nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.80,0:05:54.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的大脑就是个筛子 你是怎么知道所有事情的\N{\rEng}My brain's a sieve.How do you learn it all that stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:57.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在政府的报告上 在图书馆里\N{\rEng}It's in the government reports.It's in the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.56,0:05:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得他们会真的听我们么\N{\rEng}You think they'll really listen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.31,0:06:02.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 如果他们不听 就会有1500桶的放射性废物\N{\rEng}Well, if they don't, there's going to be 1 500 barrels of radioactive waste
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.64,0:06:03.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就埋在离这几英里的地方\N{\rEng}buried just a few miles from here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.73,0:06:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的孙子辈可能长出三个脑袋\N{\rEng}and you might have grandchildren with three heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.56,0:06:08.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 我先和你排练一下\N{\rEng}Now, look, I'm going to rehearse you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:10.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个从波因特阿里纳（加州地名）来的代表团也会去\N{\rEng}And there's a delegation from Point Arena going, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.65,0:06:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,杰利·贝克 他靠自己就很好\N{\rEng}Jerry Baker. He's very good on his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.57,0:06:14.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔也会去\N{\rEng}And Joe will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.16,0:06:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我得走了 不然就赶不上车了 好么\N{\rEng}Look, I got to go. I'll miss my ride. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.99,0:06:20.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,玛莎 记得学习小组是周四在我家\N{\rEng}Martha, remember the study group'sabcat my place on Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:21.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\rEng}Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.25,0:06:23.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么样\N{\rEng}How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.41,0:06:25.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们想要我去塔拉哈西（佛罗里达州地名）和大堂\N{\rEng}They wanted me to go to Tallahasseeabcand lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:26.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说服他们带乔和保拉去\N{\rEng}I talked them into sending Joe and Paula.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.92,0:06:28.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔和保拉\N{\rEng}Joe and Paula?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.09,0:06:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没问题 他们会很好的\N{\rEng}It's okay. They'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.92,0:06:33.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些混蛋哪来的胆量 把这些东西（指放射性废物）放在离人这么近的地方\N{\rEng}The nerve those assholes have putting that shit near human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:36.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,走吧 我要饿死了\N{\rEng}Let's blow this pop stand. I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.47,0:07:17.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们有鞋 还有两辆车来应对联邦调查局\N{\rEng}We got shoes, two cars, for feds.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.11,0:08:17.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈 乔莫还在那\N{\rEng}Mom, there's Jomo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.36,0:08:20.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你们俩 脱了牛仔裤上床\N{\rEng}You two, get out of your jeans and into bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.28,0:08:22.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她会怎么样\N{\rEng}What's gonna happen to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.70,0:08:25.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 有人会带她回家的 - 我们之前完全不需要丢下她的\N{\rEng}- Someone will take her home. - We never had to leave her before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.45,0:08:26.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起了 孩子\N{\rEng}Sorry, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:28.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他得把它留着  - 我以为我告诉你上床去了\N{\rEng}- He got to keep that. - I thought I told you to get in to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 现在是早上啊 - 上床\N{\rEng}- It's morning. - Get into bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.21,0:08:35.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要去洗头发\N{\rEng}I'm going to wash my hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:45.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是谁\N{\rEng}Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.47,0:08:48.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸妈妈 你以为是谁\N{\rEng}Mom and Dad. Who do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.47,0:08:50.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你开玩笑吧\N{\rEng}You're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.64,0:08:54.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"阿瑟和安妮·波普继续逃脱追捕\N{\rEng}"Arthur and Annie Pope continue to elude capture
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.69,0:08:57.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管这对在宣布对1971年的爆炸事件负责后\N{\rEng}"despite sightings of the couple, who went underground
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:09:01.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,转入地下的夫妻\N{\rEng}"after claiming responsibility for the 1971 bombing
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:05.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在马萨诸塞大学的军事研究所曾被发现"\N{\rEng}"of the University of Massachusetts military research lab. "
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.91,0:09:08.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"逃脱"是什么意思\N{\rEng}What does "elude" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.58,0:09:10.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没被抓到\N{\rEng}Not getting caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.41,0:09:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"该实验室是为了发展\N{\rEng}"The laboratory is credited with the development of napalm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:18.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在越战中被大规模使用的凝固汽油弹"\N{\rEng}"used extensively in the Vietnam War. "
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:20.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们为什么要炸了它（实验室）\N{\rEng}Why did they have to blow it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.34,0:09:23.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们被礼貌地要求停止制造的时候 并没有停止\N{\rEng}They didn't stop making it when they asked them politely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:25.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快点 丹尼 我是认真的\N{\rEng}Come on, Danny, I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们把那东西用在人身上\N{\rEng}They were dropping that stuff on people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:35.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"安妮·波普是从前的安妮·帕特森\N{\rEng}"Annie Pope is the former Anne Patterson
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.61,0:09:40.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国心灵传动的主席唐纳德·帕特森的女儿"\N{\rEng}"daughter of Donald Patterson, president of American Telekinetics. "
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.44,0:09:43.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是外公\N{\rEng}Is this Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 肯定是  - 那这是外婆\N{\rEng}- It must be. - And Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.71,0:09:53.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.12,0:09:56.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你记得他们么\N{\rEng}Do you remember them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:01.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 不记得  - 一点都不记得了\N{\rEng}- No. - Not even a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.47,0:10:05.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们看起来有点紧张\N{\rEng}They look kind of uptight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:11.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 到处都是工业废物\N{\rEng}- Industrial waste all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.64,0:10:14.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,趁热吃 趁新鲜\N{\rEng}Get them while they're hot.Get them before they rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.81,0:10:19.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你妈妈呢  - 她在洗澡\N{\rEng}- Where's your mother? - She's in the shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.15,0:10:26.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我今天早晨采访了一些很了解波普一家的人\N{\rEng}I talked this morning with some of the people who knew the Pope family best.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.41,0:10:28.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约翰·康格和这个在佛罗里达城\N{\rEng}John Kungle played ball with the young man
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.57,0:10:31.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被称为理查德·麦克奈利的年轻人打过球\N{\rEng}who was known here in Florida City as Richard McNally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.58,0:10:34.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是个好学生 也是个好朋友\N{\rEng}He was a good student, and a good friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.83,0:10:36.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是个好哥们\N{\rEng}He was a cool dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.33,0:10:38.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,故事就是这么编出来的\N{\rEng}That's how legends are made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.08,0:10:41.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他智商多高 49\N{\rEng}What's his IQ? 49?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:44.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他要去加州大学洛杉矶分校  - 你没开玩笑\N{\rEng}- He's going to UCLA. - No kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:47.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对 我没开玩笑 我说了他要去加州大学洛杉矶分校\N{\rEng}No, I'm not kidding.I said, he's going to UCLA.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.59,0:10:48.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.22,0:10:51.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对夫妻的这些照片看起来20岁\N{\rEng}These photos of the couple are 20 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.43,0:10:53.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且并不可靠\N{\rEng}and are not considered too reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.52,0:10:57.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对夫妻因为1971年那场使一个看门人失明的\N{\rEng}The couple is still wanted for the 1971 bombing of their university lab
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.10,0:10:59.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实验室爆炸事件仍被通缉\N{\rEng}in which a janitor was blinded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:03.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迈阿密的美国联邦调查局官员表示 尽管他们有两个孩子\N{\rEng}FBl officials in Miami said that despite the presence of their two children
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.03,0:11:07.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,波普一家仍应被认为有武装 很危险\N{\rEng}the Popes should be considered as possibly armed and dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.70,0:11:09.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在接下来的本地新闻中\N{\rEng}In further local news
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:12.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给你带了吃的\N{\rEng}There's food for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.78,0:11:14.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看起来真漂亮 妈妈\N{\rEng}You look pretty, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.12,0:11:15.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上床 小朋友\N{\rEng}Get into bed, Kimosabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.80,0:11:27.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 我们看看\N{\rEng}Okay, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.30,0:11:31.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蓝眼睛 金色头发 你可以了\N{\rEng}Blue eyes, blond hair. You're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:35.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\N{\rEng}Or are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.22,0:11:37.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了 孩子\N{\rEng}What's the matter, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.48,0:11:46.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就是觉得有点糟糕 你知道么\N{\rEng}I just feel kind of lousy, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.57,0:11:48.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,17岁的时候应该这么觉得的\N{\rEng}You're supposed to feel that way at 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.65,0:11:49.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的\N{\rEng}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:53.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你照镜子的时候都认不出你自己 这太棒了\N{\rEng}It's terrific not recognizing yourself when you look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:56.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每六个月就换一个新名字 真棒啊\N{\rEng}It's wonderful having a new name every six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.08,0:12:00.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们呆在那很长时间了 很难离开\N{\rEng}We were there a long time.It's hard to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:04.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可能还得给你剪剪头发\N{\rEng}We may have to cut your hair, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.51,0:12:11.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没准这次我还得剃光头\N{\rEng}Maybe this time I could shave my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.10,0:12:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 把你弟弟带进来  - 好\N{\rEng}- Send your brother in. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.43,0:12:21.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我讨厌这样\N{\rEng}I hate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:29.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,费城人昨晚又赢了\N{\rEng}The Phillies won again last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.11,0:12:32.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么看起来还不错\N{\rEng}Things are looking good, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:34.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好极了\N{\rEng}Things are looking great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.45,0:12:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦克阿瑟和杜鲁门有仇\N{\rEng}The MacArthur feud with Truman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.54,0:12:42.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得本地的报纸没有这个\N{\rEng}I don't think we covered that in the local paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.21,0:12:44.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许你该试试《华盛顿人》\N{\rEng}Maybe you better try The Washingtonian.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.38,0:12:47.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 我是感兴趣它对国家的中心地带有什么影响\N{\rEng}No, I'm interested in how it affected the heartland of the nation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.88,0:12:49.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些小的社区\N{\rEng}the small communities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.71,0:12:53.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这是社会史 - 我可以给你看《鹰报》\N{\rEng}- This is social history. - I could show you The Eagle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.55,0:12:56.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只是把我们过去的话题放在微缩胶片里\N{\rEng}We just put our back issues on microfilm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.22,0:13:02.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 这就是  - 把它拿到那\N{\rEng}- This is it? - Take it right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.98,0:13:03.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.51,0:13:40.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,圣马丁医院 医疗记录\N{\rEng}St. Martin's Hospital, Medical Records.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.10,0:13:45.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 三美元  - 是\N{\rEng}- Three dollars? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.10,0:13:48.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想把它寄到哪 曼斯菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}Where do you want it mailed, Mr. Mansfield?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德\N{\rEng}Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.02,0:13:51.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不用了 我自己拿\N{\rEng}No, I'll pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.53,0:13:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我需要个护照 公司要派我去开罗\N{\rEng}I need to get a passport.The company's sending me to Cairo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:56.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你做石油  - 军事\N{\rEng}- Are you in oil? - Military.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.61,0:14:01.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你现在听到的是你最喜欢的老歌频道 来自弗吉尼亚州的罗福（弗州地名）\N{\rEng}You're listening to your favorite oldies station in Norfolk, Virginia
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:12.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拉尔夫 你需要喂猫\N{\rEng}Ralph, the cat needs to be fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.12,0:15:31.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还需要什么别的吗\N{\rEng}Need anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.54,0:15:34.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 不用了 两个星期内我会再打电话的  - 好的\N{\rEng}- No. I'll call the booth again in two weeks. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.21,0:15:37.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着 你母亲\N{\rEng}Listen, your mother
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.88,0:15:41.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她四周前去世了 癌症\N{\rEng}She died four weeks ago. Cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.55,0:15:44.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你父亲当时在她身边\N{\rEng}Your father was with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:46.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你当时有麻烦 联系不上你\N{\rEng}You were just too hot to contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.47,0:15:50.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他让我告诉你不要担心他 他很好\N{\rEng}He said to tell you not to worry about him.He's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.14,0:15:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很遗憾\N{\rEng}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.28,0:16:43.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 谁要午饭\N{\rEng}Okay, who wants lunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.03,0:16:45.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我\N{\rEng}Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.28,0:16:48.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金枪鱼怎么样\N{\rEng}How's tuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.54,0:16:50.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Yecch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.70,0:16:55.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我班里有个人 要拿杜克·斯奈德（美国棒球球员）的卡和我换巴伦苏埃拉（墨西哥棒球球员）的\N{\rEng}There's a kid in my class who traded me Duke Snider for Valenzuela.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.46,0:16:57.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 所以呢\N{\rEng}Yeah, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.79,0:16:59.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以他是个混蛋\N{\rEng}So, he's a jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.13,0:17:02.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,斯奈德的卡值20美元\N{\rEng}Snider's worth about $20.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.88,0:17:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是布鲁克林道奇队的\N{\rEng}He's from the Brooklyn Dodgers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.72,0:17:07.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他老了\N{\rEng}He's old.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.39,0:17:12.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这卡是个古董\N{\rEng}This card is an antique.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.98,0:17:20.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我能要白面包么  - 吃吧\N{\rEng}- Can I have white bread?- Just eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.15,0:17:22.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 孩子\N{\rEng}Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.57,0:17:24.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你 你叫什么\N{\rEng}You. What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.82,0:17:25.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦克\N{\rEng}Michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.82,0:17:29.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你为什么问他这个  - 他还不习惯他的新名字\N{\rEng}- Why are you asking him that? - He's not used to it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.08,0:17:33.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他最好快一点习惯它\N{\rEng}He better get used to it fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.91,0:17:36.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我叫什么\N{\rEng}What's my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 保罗 - 保罗什么\N{\rEng}- Paul. - Paul what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.92,0:17:42.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 保罗·曼菲尔德  - 拼出来\N{\rEng}- Paul Manfield. - Spell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.34,0:17:47.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,M- A-N\N{\rEng}M- A-N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:52.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,F- I-E-L-D.\N{\rEng}F- I-E-L-D.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.06,0:17:54.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你妈妈叫什么  - 别问了\N{\rEng}- What's your mother's name? - Just stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.43,0:17:55.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我等你说\N{\rEng}I'm waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.02,0:17:57.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辛西娅\N{\rEng}Cynthia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:17:58.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你弟弟呢\N{\rEng}And your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.94,0:18:00.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,史蒂芬 行了吧\N{\rEng}Stephen, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.19,0:18:06.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你他妈的出什么毛病了\N{\rEng}What the hell's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.03,0:18:08.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在市内找了些衣服\N{\rEng}I got some clothes in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.78,0:18:13.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以穿二手店的这些 新的这些衣服\N{\rEng}You can wear the thrift shop ones.The new ones
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:15.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要先洗一洗\N{\rEng}have to be washed first.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.41,0:18:17.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遵命 先生\N{\rEng}Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.72,0:18:33.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天下午 对不起\N{\rEng}Sorry about this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.73,0:18:47.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我母亲苏菲去世了\N{\rEng}Sophie's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.74,0:18:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.24,0:18:55.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个月前 癌症\N{\rEng}A month ago. The big "C."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.67,0:19:01.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 宝贝\N{\rEng}Oh, babe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.21,0:19:07.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局来之后 我告诉她我们没事\N{\rEng}I talked to her after the feds came to tell her we were okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.84,0:19:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她从来没泄露我们的消息\N{\rEng}She never let on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.93,0:19:16.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我都能看见她和莫里斯站在那\N{\rEng}I can just see her standing there with Morris.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.93,0:19:19.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个胖胖的老犹太人 前布共产党\N{\rEng}Two fat old Jews, ex-Bolsheviks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在洗衣房给他们红尿布（指共产党后代）的孩子打电话\N{\rEng}talking to their red-diaper baby on a phone from a Laundromat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而她那时候已经快要去世\N{\rEng}and she's fucking dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.44,0:19:32.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那女人很爱我\N{\rEng}That lady loved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:37.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去年冬天 当他们安排我母亲在芝加哥见我的时候\N{\rEng}Last winter, when they arranged for her to meet me in Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.45,0:19:40.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她在收到通知的一个小时之内就飞了过来\N{\rEng}she flew there on an hour's notice
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.54,0:19:42.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个人 还下着暴风雪\N{\rEng}alone, in a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她很害怕坐飞机的\N{\rEng}She's terrified of flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.88,0:19:48.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她下飞机的时候脸都绿了\N{\rEng}She was green when she got off the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.71,0:19:51.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我带她到休息室聊天\N{\rEng}I took her over to the lounge to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.22,0:19:55.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们坐在角落里 我说"我希望事情容易一点"（I wish it was easier）\N{\rEng}and we sat in a corner and I said "I wish it was easier. "
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.39,0:19:59.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她说"应该说‘我希望事情容易一点（You wish it were easier）’"\N{\rEng}"You wish it were easier " she says.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.23,0:20:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她竟然在纠正我的语法错误\N{\rEng}She's correcting my grammar
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.94,0:20:06.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我是她教的小孩子一样\N{\rEng}like I'm one of the kids she teaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.86,0:20:14.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经没有让我们回去的动力了\N{\rEng}There's nothing left to go back to now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.41,0:20:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有我们和孩子们了\N{\rEng}There's only us and the boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:20.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只剩下我们了\N{\rEng}We're all that's left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.83,0:20:23.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须\N{\rEng}We must
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.91,0:20:26.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须依靠彼此\N{\rEng}We have to hang on to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.67,0:20:33.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我能看他的档案吗\N{\rEng}May I see his records?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.26,0:20:35.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我弄丢了\N{\rEng}I'm afraid I lost his records.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.43,0:20:37.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们把档案给我了 我也记得装上了\N{\rEng}They gave them to me and I know I packed them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.55,0:20:39.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是我就是找不到了\N{\rEng}but I just can't find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.68,0:20:41.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我一直丢东西 是不是\N{\rEng}I'm always losing things, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.10,0:20:45.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我丈夫说 要不是拧上了 我连头都能丢\N{\rEng}My husband says I'd probably lose my head if it weren't screwed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.52,0:20:47.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我可以重新做一份\N{\rEng}But I can write for a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.52,0:20:49.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,记得做一份档案 好吗\N{\rEng}Make sure to write for those records okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.94,0:20:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以选两节选修课\N{\rEng}You can have two electives.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:54.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,音乐 打字 机械 电脑编程 还是家政\N{\rEng}Music, typing, mechanics, computer programming, or home economics?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.11,0:20:56.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,音乐\N{\rEng}Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.11,0:20:59.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 还有呢  - 还有\N{\rEng}- And? - And?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.29,0:21:04.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 家政吧  - 他爸爸是厨师\N{\rEng}- Home economics. - His dad's a cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找个空座位 曼菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}Find an empty seat, Mr. Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.56,0:21:28.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 听着 各位\N{\rEng}All right, listen up, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.10,0:22:11.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再听一遍\N{\rEng}Listen again, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:54.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 现在有谁能告诉我这两段音乐有什么区别\N{\rEng}Now, can anyone tell me the difference between these two pieces?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.56,0:22:56.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说\N{\rEng}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.73,0:23:00.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个是流行 另一个是古典\N{\rEng}One is pop and the other is classical.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.24,0:23:04.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少我知道你不是聋子\N{\rEng}At least we know you're not deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.49,0:23:07.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得呢 斯伯丁先生\N{\rEng}How about you, Mr. Spaulding?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.99,0:23:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能不能给我们区分的更深一点\N{\rEng}Could you give us a deeper distinction?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.25,0:23:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一个很烂\N{\rEng}The first one's bad
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.92,0:23:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二个很好\N{\rEng}and the second one's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.92,0:23:19.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个观点 不是事实\N{\rEng}That's a matter of opinion, not a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.84,0:23:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这屋子里一定有好几个人不同意你的看法\N{\rEng}I'm sure there are several people in this room who would disagree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.01,0:23:27.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得呢 曼菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}How about you, Mr. Manfield?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.35,0:23:29.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,敢不敢试着说一下\N{\rEng}Would you care to venture a guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.35,0:23:37.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没法跟着贝多芬的音乐跳舞\N{\rEng}You can't dance to Beethoven.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:46.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很好 曼菲尔德先生 你听很多贝多芬的音乐\N{\rEng}That's very good, Manfield.Do you listen to much Beethoven?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:49.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 没有\N{\rEng}No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.28,0:23:51.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你怎么听出这段是贝多芬\N{\rEng}How did you identify this piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.29,0:23:54.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我猜我之前听过这段吧\N{\rEng}I guess I've heard some.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.79,0:23:58.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我确定班里的其他人也能听出另一个作者\N{\rEng}I'm sure the rest of the class can identify the other composer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.63,0:24:02.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说的很对 没法跟着贝多芬的音乐跳舞\N{\rEng}You're quite correct.abcYou can't dance to Mr. Beethoven.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.13,0:24:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能告诉我为什么吗 曼菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}Can you tell me why, Mr. Manfield?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.14,0:24:09.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为贝多芬的这段\N{\rEng}Because the Beethoven piece
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.47,0:24:13.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有一个固定的节奏 或者说拍子\N{\rEng}doesn't use a constant rhythm or tempo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.23,0:24:20.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦当娜的歌一直都是四四拍\N{\rEng}Madonna is 4/4 time all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.32,0:24:24.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋律会变 但是节奏一直不变\N{\rEng}The melody changes abcbut the rhythm is constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.49,0:24:25.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你就可以跟着它跳舞\N{\rEng}So you can dance to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.57,0:24:30.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而四重奏 是旋律和节奏都会改变\N{\rEng}The quartet changesboth melodically and rhythmically.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.74,0:24:33.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我会再放一遍 听着\N{\rEng}I'm going to play them again.Listen for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.25,0:24:42.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.34,0:24:51.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们得给你找个乐器\N{\rEng}We'll have to find an instrument for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.35,0:24:52.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乐器\N{\rEng}An instrument?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.10,0:24:56.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,选音乐课的都要在乐团演奏\N{\rEng}Everybody who takes music is required to play in the orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.19,0:25:00.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会什么乐器吗\N{\rEng}Do you play something?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.61,0:25:01.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,钢琴\N{\rEng}Piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.69,0:25:04.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弹一段\N{\rEng}Play something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.78,0:26:36.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 你没必要去乐团演奏了\N{\rEng}Well, there's one thing you don't have to do, and that's play in the orchestra.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.45,0:26:39.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想听听你在我家的斯坦威钢琴上弹的怎么样\N{\rEng}I'd like to hear how you sound on the Steinway I have at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.79,0:26:43.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出去吧\N{\rEng}Get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.05,0:26:58.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 找到工作了 爸爸  - 找到了 就在城里\N{\rEng}- Get a job, Dad? - You betcha I did. Right in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.22,0:27:01.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我是厨师 猜是做什么菜  - 意大利菜\N{\rEng}- I'm a cook. Guess which kind? - Italian?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.14,0:27:03.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 猜对啦  - 太棒了\N{\rEng}- You got it. - Radical!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.39,0:27:05.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非得这么说话么\N{\rEng}Do you have to say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.90,0:27:10.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 从哪拿到这个的  - 公共图书馆的失物招领处\N{\rEng}- Where'd you get this? - Public library lost and found.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.65,0:27:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就在餐厅的转角处\N{\rEng}It's right around the corner from the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.40,0:27:15.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这四月会很冷 我觉得你用得到\N{\rEng}April can be cold up here.I thought you might needthese.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.99,0:27:18.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别让你这双拿球棒的手冻裂了\N{\rEng}Keep those slugger hands from cracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.49,0:27:20.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 进球队了么  - 嗯\N{\rEng}- Did you make the team? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.24,0:27:22.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 太棒了 - 我有什么\N{\rEng}- Great. - What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.50,0:27:26.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起 孩子 东西都没有你的号 周末我去电影院试试\N{\rEng}Sorry, kid. Nothing in your size. Have to try a movie theater on the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.17,0:27:28.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这提醒了我 周六得去砍些柴火\N{\rEng}Which reminds me, we have to chop some firewood on Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.75,0:27:30.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 爸爸 我明天做这个 明天我不上学\N{\rEng}Oh, Dad, I'll do it tomorrow.I'm not going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.92,0:27:32.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 为什么  - 他们在拍班级合照\N{\rEng}- How come? - They're taking class pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.09,0:27:34.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.17,0:27:37.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 那学校怎么样  - 还不错\N{\rEng}- How is that school? - Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.59,0:27:41.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 老师知道点你不知道的东西  - 嗯 他们还不错\N{\rEng}- Teachers know anything you don't? - Yeah, they're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.10,0:27:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你注册的时候遇到麻烦了吗\N{\rEng}Did you have any trouble with the registration?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.93,0:27:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天放学的时候我去见了辅导员\N{\rEng}I had to see the guidance counselor at the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.19,0:27:47.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢\N{\rEng}And?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.35,0:27:50.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他想知道我要申请哪个大学\N{\rEng}He wanted to know what colleges I was applying to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.11,0:27:52.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你告诉他什么了\N{\rEng}What did you tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.69,0:27:54.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,呃 我说我还没决定\N{\rEng}Well, I said I hadn't decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.28,0:27:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 就和他们随便说点什么 然后忘了吧\N{\rEng}Good. Just tell them something, and forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.70,0:27:59.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不然他们会一直偷听你\N{\rEng}Otherwise they'll keep bugging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.78,0:28:03.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你怎么样 小东西  - 我不要胡椒\N{\rEng}- How about you, small stuff? - I don't want peppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.71,0:28:12.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上帝保佑\N{\rEng}Bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.13,0:28:18.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们班有个人真的很疯狂\N{\rEng}There's a kid in my class who's really crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.39,0:28:22.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的精神又没正常到哪去\N{\rEng}You're not exactly the poster child for mental health.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.14,0:28:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他记得火车时刻表\N{\rEng}He knows train schedules.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.97,0:28:26.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你从来不需要知道 你可以在手里有一份 然后就都知道了\N{\rEng}You never know.It might have come in handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.73,0:28:29.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的 爸爸 整个国家的他都知道\N{\rEng}Really, Dad. All over the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.56,0:28:33.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他知道火车什么时候从奥马哈到佐治亚州的亚特兰大\N{\rEng}He knows what time trains leave from Omaha to Atlanta, Georgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.23,0:28:34.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像这样的东西\N{\rEng}Stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.32,0:28:36.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得认识认识这孩子 你拿着这别针干什么呢\N{\rEng}Get to know this kid.What are you doing with that safety pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.99,0:28:38.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么别针\N{\rEng}What safety pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.83,0:28:44.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我找到工作了  - 真的\N{\rEng}- I got a job. - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.49,0:28:46.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我们 亲爱的\N{\rEng}Tell us, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.00,0:28:50.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要怎么奉献这个虚假的资本主义经济\N{\rEng}How are you going to contribute to this false, capitalist economy?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.83,0:28:54.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要做一个米尔顿·克斯维尔医生的接待员\N{\rEng}I'm going to be a receptionist for a Dr. Milton Cosswell.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.42,0:28:55.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是吗  - 对\N{\rEng}- Yeah? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.59,0:28:57.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,邮局有个招聘的告示\N{\rEng}There was a sign up at the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.67,0:28:59.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他不介意付我现金\N{\rEng}He doesn't mind paying me in cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.34,0:29:01.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他甚至都没问为什么\N{\rEng}He didn't even ask why.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.01,0:29:04.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,应该是对他避税还是什么的有好处吧\N{\rEng}It's probably good for his taxes, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.18,0:29:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管怎么样 有工作意味着如果我们需要 就可以拿点东西来用\N{\rEng}Anyway, it means I can pick up supplies, if we need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.52,0:29:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他看起来是个好人\N{\rEng}He seems like a pretty nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.19,0:29:17.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢妈妈\N{\rEng}Mom, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.11,0:29:22.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着不错 看起来我们都得到想要的东西了\N{\rEng}Sounds good. Looks like we all got what we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.54,0:30:53.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人在家吗\N{\rEng}Hello, is anyone home?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.05,0:31:07.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有人吗\N{\rEng}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.00,0:33:08.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是谁\N{\rEng}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.76,0:33:10.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是住这的 那你是谁\N{\rEng}I live here. Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.93,0:33:14.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 菲利普斯先生是你父亲  - 是\N{\rEng}- Is Mr. Phillips your father? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.18,0:33:16.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿粉色衣服的这是你\N{\rEng}And is this you in the pink-
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.76,0:33:17.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 别想它了\N{\rEng}I've destroyed the negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.10,0:33:20.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在你知道我是这的人了 该说说你了\N{\rEng}So now we've determined that I belong here. Let's talk about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.27,0:33:24.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你父亲说我可以弹他的钢琴 而且门是开着的\N{\rEng}Your father said I could use the piano. And the door was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.85,0:33:27.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们有门铃的 - 我按门铃了\N{\rEng}- We do have a bell. - I rang the bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.44,0:33:30.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没人应 我就进来了 对不起\N{\rEng}No one answered, so I came in. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.53,0:33:32.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在我父亲的学校\N{\rEng}You go to the school?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.45,0:33:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.61,0:33:36.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我没见过你  - 那是因为我刚来\N{\rEng}- I haven't seen you there. - That's because I just started.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.95,0:33:38.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你今天怎么没去上学\N{\rEng}So how come you're not there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.62,0:33:42.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我昨晚发烧了 我妈让我呆在家里\N{\rEng}I had a fever last night.My mom made me stay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.37,0:33:45.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 那你为什么不呆在家里  - 我今天好多了 还很无聊\N{\rEng}- Why didn't you? - I felt better today. And I was bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.79,0:33:49.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你真奇怪 我今天翘课了\N{\rEng}You're strange. I cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.21,0:33:52.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我可不想和这些非人类一块拍照\N{\rEng}I didn't feel like having my picture taken with those subhumans.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.72,0:33:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你很好 你知道\N{\rEng}You're very good, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.38,0:33:56.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我还可以\N{\rEng}I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.80,0:33:58.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你叫什么\N{\rEng}What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.64,0:34:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 麦克  - 我叫罗娜\N{\rEng}- Michael. - I'm Lorna.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.64,0:34:02.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我还是走吧\N{\rEng}I'd better be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.89,0:34:05.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你从哪来  - 奥克兰\N{\rEng}- Where are you from? - Oakland.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.31,0:34:07.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你生在加州  - 不 纽约\N{\rEng}- You born in California?- No, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.23,0:34:09.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的\N{\rEng}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.48,0:34:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想去纽约上学 但我妈妈怕我被抢劫\N{\rEng}I want to go to school in New York, but my mother's afraid I'll get mugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.65,0:34:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你家经常搬\N{\rEng}Your family move around a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.49,0:34:16.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 不是 你弹钢琴么\N{\rEng}No, not really. You play?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.66,0:34:19.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天哪 不 我可受不了练琴\N{\rEng}God, no. I couldn't stand to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.16,0:34:22.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我哥哥是演奏家\N{\rEng}My older brother is the virtuoso.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.83,0:34:26.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他上耶鲁 他做什么都对 你要去哪个大学\N{\rEng}He's at Yale. He does everything right.Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.92,0:34:33.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 那个啊 我还没怎么想过\N{\rEng}Oh, that.I haven't thought about that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.01,0:34:37.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还没怎么想过 下个学期可就要申请了\N{\rEng}You haven't though about it much? You're going to have to apply next semester.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.85,0:34:41.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是么\N{\rEng}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.85,0:34:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你什么意思 "是么"\N{\rEng}What do you mean, "Yeah?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.02,0:34:49.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看 我真的, 真的得走了\N{\rEng}Look, I really, I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.86,0:34:52.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你很有资格\N{\rEng}You're certifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.03,0:34:54.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不用谢\N{\rEng}You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.78,0:35:03.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德先生 我想和你说句话\N{\rEng}Mr. Manfield, I'd like a word with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.54,0:35:10.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你昨天去了我家\N{\rEng}I understand you had occasion to visit my house yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.04,0:35:12.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我去看你的钢琴了\N{\rEng}I went to look at your piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.88,0:35:15.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你不只是看看而已\N{\rEng}I understand you did more than look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.13,0:35:18.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你家里有钢琴吗  - 没有 先生\N{\rEng}- Do you have a piano at home? - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.64,0:35:20.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你怎么练习\N{\rEng}How do you practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.72,0:35:23.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能常练\N{\rEng}I can't much.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.72,0:35:26.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是个很有才华的音乐家 曼菲尔德\N{\rEng}You're a talented musician, Manfield
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.64,0:35:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但你没有像罪犯一样（进别人家）的权利\N{\rEng}but that doesn't give you theright to act like a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.14,0:35:30.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,清楚了吗\N{\rEng}Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.90,0:35:33.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是的 先生\N{\rEng}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.61,0:35:38.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德\N{\rEng}Manfield?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.99,0:35:42.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会给你找个钢琴\N{\rEng}We'll find you a piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.12,0:35:52.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我看看 姑娘们\N{\rEng}Now let me see, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.09,0:35:59.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 去队尾吧\N{\rEng}Thank you. Just go to the back of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.59,0:36:03.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你很有资格啊\N{\rEng}You are certifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.72,0:36:07.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是怎么回事 开什么玩笑 你上厨艺课\N{\rEng}What is this? Some sort of smart-ass joke? You're taking cooking?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.77,0:36:09.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想学做菜\N{\rEng}I want to learn how to cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.18,0:36:13.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 对 你有强烈的欲望想学怎么做Apple Brown Betty（一种用苹果和面包屑制成的甜点）\N{\rEng}Yeah, right. You have a burning desire to learn how to make Apple Brown Betty.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.36,0:36:16.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你要是这么想 那你在这干什么\N{\rEng}What are you doing here if you think so highly of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.44,0:36:18.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们不让我学机械\N{\rEng}They wouldn't let me take auto mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.44,0:36:20.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我也没时间把这事告到最高法院\N{\rEng}and I didn't have time to take the issue to the Supreme Court.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.03,0:36:24.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既然剩下了菲利普斯和曼菲尔德\N{\rEng}Now that leaves Phillips and Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.87,0:36:27.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你们可以用最后一张台吗\N{\rEng}Please, would you take the last booth?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.62,0:36:31.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天的菜谱\N{\rEng}Today's menu
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.08,0:36:35.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是金枪鱼核桃砂锅\N{\rEng}is tuna-walnut casserole.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.13,0:36:37.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这大概也算是机械吧\N{\rEng}This may be auto mechanics after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:40.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拿着四杯量的量杯\N{\rEng}Take your four-cup measuring bowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.67,0:36:43.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我父亲觉得你是切片面包之外最好的东西\N{\rEng}You know, my father thinks you're the best thing since sliced bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.47,0:36:45.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他可不是这么对我说的\N{\rEng}That's not what he told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.80,0:36:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一罐金枪鱼\N{\rEng}A can of tuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.64,0:36:49.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着 别担心 别让他吓着你\N{\rEng}Listen, don't worry.Don't let him scare you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.56,0:36:51.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果他觉得你可以演奏 你就可以为所欲为了\N{\rEng}You can do anything if he thinks you can play music.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.56,0:36:54.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,半杯核桃\N{\rEng}Half a cup of walnuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.27,0:36:57.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,周六有室内乐演奏会\N{\rEng}We're having a chamber music concert Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.90,0:37:00.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无聊的要死 你还得穿的像去葬礼一样\N{\rEng}And they're boring as hell, you have to dress for a funeral
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.32,0:37:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是你应该会喜欢 想来吗\N{\rEng}but you'd probably like it.abcYou want to come?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.90,0:37:03.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两根芹菜\N{\rEng}Two stalks of celery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.57,0:37:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好 我考虑考虑 芹菜  - 芹菜\N{\rEng}- Yeah, I've got to think about it. Celery. - Celery.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.16,0:37:09.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这\N{\rEng}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.08,0:37:14.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他被那些资产阶级的垃圾引诱了\N{\rEng}He's getting seduced by all this bourgeois crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.08,0:37:17.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 去他的室内乐 - 那是音乐啊 看在上帝的份上\N{\rEng}- Fucking chamber music. - It's music, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.17,0:37:20.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,颓废的 白皮肤的 特权阶级的垃圾\N{\rEng}Decadent, white-skinned, privileged crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.67,0:37:24.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一大堆人打着领带穿着连裤袜坐着扶手椅 呆在一块\N{\rEng}Lot of people sitting around in ties and pantyhose in wing chairs
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.09,0:37:26.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 像在你母亲家 - 像在我母亲家\N{\rEng}- like at your mother's house. - Like at my mother's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.18,0:37:27.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他不能去\N{\rEng}He's not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.01,0:37:30.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谁说的  - 我说的\N{\rEng}- Says who? - Says me!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.10,0:37:33.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不信  - 看我的口型：他不能去\N{\rEng}- I don't believe you. - Read my lips: He's not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.77,0:37:35.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你什么时候成了文化部长\N{\rEng}Since when did you become the minister of culture?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.02,0:37:37.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果是摇滚演唱会你就让他去了\N{\rEng}You'd let him go if it was a rock 'n' roll concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.02,0:37:40.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 对了 我会的 对  - 难以置信\N{\rEng}- That's right! You bet I would. Yes. - Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.27,0:37:42.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你神经错乱了吗\N{\rEng}Are you out of your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.78,0:37:46.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不会让他去的 因为不安全\N{\rEng}I'm not letting him go because it's not safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.91,0:37:50.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他又不至于暴露在整个沃特福德面前\N{\rEng}He doesn't have to be on display for the entire community of Waterford.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.37,0:37:54.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且就因为这不是摇滚演唱会\N{\rEng}And because it's not rock and roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.96,0:37:58.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你以为你很可爱 爸爸 但你就是垃圾\N{\rEng}You think you're cute, Dad but you're full of shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.29,0:38:02.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 不要对我这样讲话  - 为什么\N{\rEng}- Don't talk to me like that. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.55,0:38:04.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不应该质疑权威么 你就是那么教我的\N{\rEng}Aren't we supposed to question authority? You taught me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.05,0:38:07.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你以为你是谁 巴顿将军\N{\rEng}Who do you think you are? General Patton?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.13,0:38:10.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么上学对我来说还比去音乐会危险了\N{\rEng}Why is it any more dangerous for me to go to school than it is to go to the concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.55,0:38:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为在学校还有600个孩子\N{\rEng}Because there are 600 other kids at the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.35,0:38:17.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我歇会吧\N{\rEng}Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.48,0:38:19.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不可以去\N{\rEng}You're not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.65,0:39:48.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德先生 我们有这样的享受应该感谢什么\N{\rEng}Mr. Manfield! To what do we owe this pleasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.90,0:39:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,罗娜邀请的我\N{\rEng}Lorna invited me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.65,0:39:53.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她通常没这么好的审美\N{\rEng}She usually doesn't show such good judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.66,0:39:56.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴 我想让你见一些人\N{\rEng}I'm delighted. There's some people I want you to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.33,0:39:59.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,山姆 这是麦克·曼菲尔德 我和你说过的那个男孩\N{\rEng}Sam, this is Michael Manfield the boy I was telling you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.83,0:40:00.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 很高兴认识你  - 你好\N{\rEng}- Pleased to meet you. - Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.91,0:40:03.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许我们可以让你给我们弹点什么\N{\rEng}Perhaps we can convince you to play something for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.33,0:40:05.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我什么都没准备\N{\rEng}I have nothing prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一天我听见你在弹勃拉姆斯 真是美\N{\rEng}I heard you working on some Brahms the other day. It was perfectly lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.59,0:40:10.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二次幕间休息之后你可以弹一弹\N{\rEng}You can play it after the second intermission.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.51,0:40:14.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很乐意 但是我真的要去朋友家接我弟弟\N{\rEng}I'd like to, but I really have to go pick up my brother at a friend's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.34,0:40:16.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以在走之前弹\N{\rEng}You can play before you have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.35,0:40:17.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听着 爸爸 抱歉\N{\rEng}Listen, Dad, would you excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.51,0:40:18.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想带麦克吃点东西\N{\rEng}I'd like to get Michael something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.76,0:40:21.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 希望早点听到你演奏 - 真是好东西\N{\rEng}- Hope to hear you soon. - It was really good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.86,0:40:31.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么你不想为他们演奏\N{\rEng}How come you didn't want to play for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.78,0:40:36.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果是我自己 我不会考虑 但是你会喜欢的\N{\rEng}Personally, I wouldn't consider it but you're supposed to love this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.29,0:40:43.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没关系 你不用解释 莫扎特也是个疯子\N{\rEng}It's all right. You don't have to explain.Mozart was crazy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.88,0:40:48.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 想上去去我的房间么  - 好\N{\rEng}- Want to go up to my room? - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.04,0:40:51.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好啦 把牛奶喝完\N{\rEng}All right. Finish your milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.32,0:41:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.32,0:41:18.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吉他就是我的生命\N{\rEng}Guitar is my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.50,0:41:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你很让人迷惑 你知道\N{\rEng}You're very confusing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.67,0:41:33.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁 我 为什么\N{\rEng}Who, me? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.67,0:41:35.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为有的时候你那么直接\N{\rEng}'Cause sometimes you can be so straight
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.34,0:41:37.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有的时候 转过身去你又是那样的\N{\rEng}and then other times, you turn around and you're like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.60,0:41:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 总是说着"是 先生"或者"不是 先生" - 我很礼貌的\N{\rEng}-It's always, "Yes, sir" and "No, sir. " - I'm polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.85,0:41:49.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 礼貌很假  - 不是假\N{\rEng}- Polite is phony. - It's not phony.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.02,0:41:54.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 可以避免冲突  - 你现在就在做这个么\N{\rEng}- It avoids confrontation. - Is that what you're doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.19,0:41:56.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在避免冲突\N{\rEng}You're avoiding confrontation?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.45,0:41:58.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就没有想说"去他妈的"的时候\N{\rEng}Don't you ever want to say, "Cut the shit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.70,0:42:01.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,罗娜 麦克和你在一起吗 我想让他出来演奏\N{\rEng}Lorna! Is Michael in there with you? I want him to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.29,0:42:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他走了 他去接他弟弟了\N{\rEng}He left. He went to pick up his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.58,0:42:09.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以为这是我的房间\N{\rEng}I thought this was my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.46,0:42:13.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈让你下楼\N{\rEng}Your mother wants you downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.56,0:42:26.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那有棵树（可以从那出去）\N{\rEng}There's a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.19,0:43:18.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲍威尔太太 可以见医生了\N{\rEng}Mrs. Powell? The doctor will see you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.53,0:43:25.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我把钱包落在这了吗\N{\rEng}Did I leave my purse out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.29,0:43:29.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.54,0:43:33.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\rEng}Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.54,0:43:35.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\rEng}Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.63,0:43:38.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你有预约吗\N{\rEng}Do you have an appointment?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.55,0:43:41.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.56,0:43:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,格斯\N{\rEng}Gus!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.23,0:44:00.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吃什么 妈妈\N{\rEng}What's cooking, mama?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.82,0:44:05.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我看着你 我就能看到你站在密歇根街角\N{\rEng}I look at you, and I can see you standing on the corner of Michigan Avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.07,0:44:09.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,穿着墨西哥式上衣 戴着那疯癫的银色东西\N{\rEng}in a Mexican blouse and those crazy silver things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.41,0:44:11.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大银耳环\N{\rEng}Big silver earrings.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.25,0:44:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天哪 那是好久以前了\N{\rEng}God, that was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.67,0:44:17.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿瑟怎么样\N{\rEng}How's Artie?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.92,0:44:19.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他挺好\N{\rEng}He's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.09,0:44:22.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实他好极了\N{\rEng}He's great, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.09,0:44:26.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他在佛罗里达的一处有毒垃圾堆放点做了点工作\N{\rEng}He did some work in Florida on a toxic waste dump.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.84,0:44:29.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这 他组织了个个食品公司\N{\rEng}Here, he organized a food co-op
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.68,0:44:31.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他还在让他的餐厅集团化\N{\rEng}and he's trying to get his restaurant to unionize.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.68,0:44:33.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和阿瑟怎么样\N{\rEng}And how's you and Artie?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.60,0:44:35.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还好\N{\rEng}We're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.85,0:44:40.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 你知道 很艰难\N{\rEng}I mean, you know, it's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.69,0:44:42.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想你\N{\rEng}I think about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.11,0:44:45.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想你\N{\rEng}I think about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.16,0:44:49.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,希望你是安全的\N{\rEng}I hope you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.04,0:44:53.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么做到的\N{\rEng}How do you manage this?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.20,0:44:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有房子\N{\rEng}Got a house
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.04,0:44:57.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个孩子\N{\rEng}two kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.38,0:45:00.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像你过着正常人的生活\N{\rEng}It's kind of like you're leading a regular life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.80,0:45:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我很会撒谎\N{\rEng}I'm a good liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.84,0:45:06.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我累了\N{\rEng}But I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.51,0:45:11.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈的\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.15,0:45:19.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 天\N{\rEng}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.07,0:45:28.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 大厨\N{\rEng}Hey, chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.99,0:45:30.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\rEng}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.16,0:45:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你好\N{\rEng}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.08,0:45:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个人开了八百英里来见你\N{\rEng}That's all you got to say to this guy that just drove
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.66,0:45:39.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就和他说一句你好\N{\rEng}800 miles out of his way to see you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.75,0:45:41.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看起来好极了\N{\rEng}You look great.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.17,0:45:43.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么我会感觉这么不安\N{\rEng}Then how come I feel so uneasy?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.17,0:45:46.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿瑟 我们去散步吧 我有事情要告诉你\N{\rEng}Artie, let's take a walk.I got stuff to talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.59,0:45:47.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我累了\N{\rEng}I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.76,0:45:51.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去吧 保罗 和他散散步 你有12年没见他了\N{\rEng}Go ahead, Paul. Take a walk with him. You haven't seen him for 12 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.03,0:46:07.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你他妈的是疯了\N{\rEng}You're out of your fucking mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.94,0:46:10.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你欠我们的  - 我他妈的什么都不欠你们\N{\rEng}- You owe us! - I don't owe you a goddamn thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.20,0:46:13.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你那混蛋朋友想让我干什么吗\N{\rEng}Do you know what your asshole friend here wants me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.20,0:46:18.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抢银行 你相信么 他妈的银行\N{\rEng}Rob a fucking bank! Can you believe it? A fucking bank!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.29,0:46:21.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他还说那是"政治运动"\N{\rEng}A "political action " he calls it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.79,0:46:24.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自由军布置给我们这个任务的\N{\rEng}We've been assigned this little job by the Liberation Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.79,0:46:27.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别人都对他们有错误的印象 以为他们在支持我们\N{\rEng}Who are under the mistaken impression that they've been supporting us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.80,0:46:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们欠他们的\N{\rEng}and we owe them something!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.47,0:46:32.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想让我的孩子做什么\N{\rEng}What do they want my kids to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.64,0:46:34.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,推翻他妈的总统\N{\rEng}Knock off the fucking president?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.81,0:46:37.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想让我看看你车里是什么吗\N{\rEng}You want to show what you got in your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.98,0:46:41.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没什么 我的东西\N{\rEng}Nothing. It's my stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.48,0:46:43.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这可不是你给我的印象\N{\rEng}That's not the impression you gave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.15,0:46:46.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看吧 怎么样\N{\rEng}Let's look, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.15,0:46:48.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让孩子们过来 我想让他们看看这个\N{\rEng}Get the kids down here.I want them to see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.90,0:46:50.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这人还他妈是个疯子\N{\rEng}guy's still a fucking maniac!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.90,0:46:51.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闭嘴吧\N{\rEng}Just stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.07,0:46:55.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们 过来 就现在\N{\rEng}Boys! Get down here! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.85,0:47:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想让你们知道 我们不动枪\N{\rEng}I want you to know guns are not what we're about.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.11,0:47:27.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 回屋里去\N{\rEng}Now, get back in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.45,0:47:40.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会改变世界的 阿瑟\N{\rEng}You're going to change the world, Artie
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.45,0:47:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就组织一下那几个小食品公司\N{\rEng}by organizing these little food co-ops?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.96,0:47:49.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要出去\N{\rEng}I'm going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.38,0:47:53.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你晚上可以留下\N{\rEng}You can stay the night
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.13,0:47:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但等我回来 我可不想看见这些枪在我孩子周围十公里以内\N{\rEng}but when I get back, I don't want to see these things within 10 miles of my kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.24,0:48:19.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安妮 我想解释\N{\rEng}Annie, I'd like to explain this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.99,0:48:22.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在听\N{\rEng}I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.58,0:48:26.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我们在地下状态已经很久了\N{\rEng}You know, we've been under a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.92,0:48:31.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多不好的事情发生了 很多不好的事情还在发生\N{\rEng}A lot of bad shit has happened. A lot of bad shit keeps happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.92,0:48:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是整个世界都以为\N{\rEng}But we're dead
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.93,0:48:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经死了\N{\rEng}as far as the world is concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.51,0:48:44.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们采取一个行动 报纸就埋没一个\N{\rEng}We pull an action and they bury it in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.68,0:48:47.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就好像什么都没发生过\N{\rEng}It's like it didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.52,0:48:51.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有在什么东西或者什么人被吹走了\N{\rEng}The only time the pigs or the media pay attention
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.44,0:48:54.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那猪一样的媒体才会引起注意\N{\rEng}is when something or somebody gets blown away.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.61,0:48:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好 如果打不败他们 就加入他们\N{\rEng}Great. If you can't beat them, join them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.78,0:49:03.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得我们采取非暴力 会取得胜利么\N{\rEng}Do you think we're going to win this by turning the other cheek?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.79,0:49:07.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要是能这样 你怎么不试试在水上走\N{\rEng}Why don't you try walking on water?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.96,0:49:11.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么还不长大呢 我们赢不了的\N{\rEng}Why don't you try growing up? There's nothing to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.13,0:49:14.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,战争一结束 它已经结束了\N{\rEng}It was over as soon as the war ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.96,0:49:18.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,战争没有结束 安妮 它永远不会结束\N{\rEng}The war didn't end, Annie.The war ain't never going to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.97,0:49:23.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和政治或者我车里的货无关\N{\rEng}This has nothing to do with politics or the merchandise in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.97,0:49:25.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是阿瑟发火了\N{\rEng}This is just Artie's pissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.98,0:49:30.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿瑟发火了\N{\rEng}Artie's pissed
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.56,0:49:32.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为他嫉妒\N{\rEng}'cause Artie's jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.40,0:49:37.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他嫉妒\N{\rEng}And Artie's jealous
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.91,0:49:42.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为你想要我\N{\rEng}because you want me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.08,0:49:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我当然也想要你\N{\rEng}And I sure want you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.08,0:49:51.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这状况真糟糕\N{\rEng}That's a bad situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.84,0:49:57.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,迟早它们都会爆炸\N{\rEng}Sooner or later, they're just going to blow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.76,0:50:03.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我为你感到遗憾\N{\rEng}You know, I feel sorry for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.18,0:50:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的\N{\rEng}I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.01,0:50:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你46岁了 还像个婴儿\N{\rEng}You're a 46-year-old infant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.52,0:50:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么都得按着你的想法来 是不是 什么时候都是 什么地方都是\N{\rEng}Everything has to be your way, doesn't it? When you want it, where you want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.27,0:50:18.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不是革命者\N{\rEng}You're not a revolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.19,0:50:22.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这比玩枪或者玩弄自己要求更高\N{\rEng}That requires more than playing with guns or with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.37,0:50:27.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要同情心 需要纪律\N{\rEng}It requires compassion, discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.37,0:50:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在评判我么\N{\rEng}Are you judging me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.46,0:50:38.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,女士 你在评判你自己\N{\rEng}You judge yourself, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.13,0:50:44.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你过得就像那种傻乎乎的中产阶级的郊区家庭主妇\N{\rEng}You're living like some kind of silly-ass, middle-class, suburban housewife.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.64,0:50:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你活在谎言之中\N{\rEng}You're living a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.31,0:50:52.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像你说的那样\N{\rEng}just like you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.48,0:50:59.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么不把诺曼·洛克威尔一家供出来\N{\rEng}Why don't you take this little Norman Rockwell family and turn them in?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.65,0:51:02.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局会很乐意抓到他们的\N{\rEng}The feds would be glad to get them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.82,0:51:05.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样你就可以脱身了\N{\rEng}And then you could get the fuck out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.99,0:51:10.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我倒希望我能\N{\rEng}I wish I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.00,0:51:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出去吧\N{\rEng}Now get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.03,0:51:43.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还好么 妈妈\N{\rEng}Are you okay, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.20,0:51:46.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.28,0:51:48.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.72,0:52:07.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,睡觉吧\N{\rEng}Go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.93,0:52:56.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不是保罗 我不是保罗 我是\N{\rEng}I am not Paul. I am not Paul! I am-
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.85,0:53:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 进来 保罗  - 我不是保罗\N{\rEng}- Paul, come in. - I'm not Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.11,0:53:04.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是阿瑟\N{\rEng}I'm Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.77,0:53:07.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别叫我"保罗" 我是阿瑟\N{\rEng}Don't call me "Paul. " I am Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.69,0:53:10.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是阿瑟·艾利·波普\N{\rEng}I am Arthur Eli Pope!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.45,0:53:13.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 爸爸怎么了  - 他刚喝多了\N{\rEng}- What's the matter with Dad? - He's just had a lot to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.03,0:53:18.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1944年7月16日出生在纽约州的普拉茨堡\N{\rEng}Born in Plattsburg, New York, July 16, 1944!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.54,0:53:22.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国公民, 我母亲\N{\rEng}A US citizen. My mother's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.71,0:53:25.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,娘家姓是希尔伯维茨\N{\rEng}maiden name is Silbowitz.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.29,0:53:28.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我父亲真名是波波夫 莫里斯·波波夫\N{\rEng}My father's real name is Popov.Morris Popov.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.13,0:53:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我驾驶证号码是4-3-5-7\N{\rEng}My driver's license number is 4-3-5-7
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.55,0:53:34.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1-1\N{\rEng}1-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.80,0:53:38.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我入伍时候的号码是M-S-8-9\N{\rEng}My draft number is M-S-8-9
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.81,0:53:42.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 好了\N{\rEng}- 3-5-8-4. -3-5-8-4. - It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.31,0:53:45.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我叫波普\N{\rEng}My name is Pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.48,0:53:46.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没事了\N{\rEng}It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.76,0:54:17.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说要散步 又不是远足\N{\rEng}You said walk, not hike.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.43,0:54:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你累了  - 不是\N{\rEng}- Are you tired? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.94,0:54:30.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 很美  - 是啊\N{\rEng}-It's beautiful. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.45,0:54:35.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 当你约我的时候我真的很惊讶\N{\rEng}You know, I was really surprised when you called me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.03,0:54:38.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么\N{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.95,0:54:41.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不确定你是不是喜欢我\N{\rEng}I wasn't sure if you liked me or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.45,0:54:45.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的时候你那么\N{\rEng}Sometimes you're so
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.04,0:54:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遥远\N{\rEng}distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.46,0:54:52.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我也不确定你是不是也很喜欢我\N{\rEng}I'm not too sure if you like me too much, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.55,0:54:58.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信吧 我可不会跟着一个我不喜欢的人走上十英里\N{\rEng}Take it on faith. I usually don't follow people I don't like for 10 miles
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.80,0:55:00.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直走到树林中间\N{\rEng}into the middle of the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.39,0:55:01.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么这么生气\N{\rEng}Why are you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.72,0:55:04.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是风趣 不是生气\N{\rEng}That's wit, not anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.56,0:55:08.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你吓到很多人  - 除了你还有谁\N{\rEng}- You scare a lot of people. - Who, besides you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.90,0:55:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多人吓到我\N{\rEng}A lot of people scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.90,0:55:16.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁吓到你\N{\rEng}Who scares you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.58,0:55:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像我父母一样和善的人\N{\rEng}People who are nice, like my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.25,0:55:28.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和善的人有什么错\N{\rEng}What's wrong with being nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.92,0:55:30.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样说吧\N{\rEng}Let's put it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.84,0:55:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我母亲真的很好\N{\rEng}My mother is really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.76,0:55:37.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她从来不做任何错事或者刻薄的事\N{\rEng}She never does anything wrong or mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.51,0:55:41.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她甚至把旧衣服给仆人\N{\rEng}She even gives her old clothe to the maid
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.93,0:55:45.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但她真的不想认识她\N{\rEng}but she doesn't really want to know her.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.27,0:55:47.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,十年里她连贝蒂的丈夫都没见过\N{\rEng}In 10 years she's never even seen Betty's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.19,0:55:51.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他来接她的时候都在车里等着\N{\rEng}He waits in the car when he comes to pick her up.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.69,0:55:56.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你父亲一定不像这样\N{\rEng}Your father's sure not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.03,0:55:58.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么 因为他在课上放麦当娜的歌\N{\rEng}Why? Because he plays Madonna in class?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.03,0:56:01.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他除了知道你弹琴很棒 还知道什么\N{\rEng}What does he know about you, except that you're good on the piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.37,0:56:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们只看到他们想看的东西 把别的都屏蔽掉\N{\rEng}They see what they want to see and they block out everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.79,0:56:08.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是可能不太好的东西\N{\rEng}especially if it might not be nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.54,0:56:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们好像并不很习惯你的方式\N{\rEng}They don't seem to get in your way much.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.54,0:56:14.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我父母 他们的方式就是不相信我真正的样子\N{\rEng}My parents? It's just their way of not believing who I really am.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.13,0:56:17.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们觉得最终我会变成\N{\rEng}They think that eventually I'll turn back into the little girl
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.80,0:56:20.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,钢琴上的照片里那穿着粉色裙子的小女孩\N{\rEng}in the pink dress that's in the picture on the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.72,0:56:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你觉得呢\N{\rEng}And what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.89,0:56:27.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你真的想知道\N{\rEng}You really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.89,0:56:31.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得我会去纽约学写作\N{\rEng}I think that I'll go to New York and learn to write
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.98,0:56:34.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个圣诞节回家\N{\rEng}and that I'll come home every Christmas
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.57,0:56:37.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大家都对我很礼貌\N{\rEng}and everyone will be really polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.57,0:56:40.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听起来没那么坏\N{\rEng}That's doesn't sound so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.82,0:56:44.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是 但是我还没真正在纽约\N{\rEng}Maybe not, but I'm not in New York yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.75,0:56:52.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你呢\N{\rEng}So what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.75,0:56:55.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我完全不了解你\N{\rEng}I don't know a thing about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.75,0:56:59.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能会完好地从宙斯的脑袋里钻出来（指雅典娜）\N{\rEng}You might as well have sprung full-grown out of the head of Zeus.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.76,0:57:01.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你父母呢 奥兹和哈里特 （电影《奥兹和哈里特的冒险》 奥兹和哈里特生活在数字时代）\N{\rEng}Who are your parents? Ozzie and Harriet?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.26,0:57:03.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 有时候是这样\N{\rEng}Yeah, sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.76,0:57:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是不是得去见见他们 看看你为什么这么完美\N{\rEng}Do I get to meet them and see how you came out so perfect?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.18,0:57:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的意思是 这样才公平\N{\rEng}I mean, it seems only fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.52,0:57:11.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我让你看我的 你让我看你的\N{\rEng}I showed you mine, you show me yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.61,0:57:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我猜这就结束休息了吧\N{\rEng}I guess this is the end of the rest stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.28,0:57:24.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说什么来着\N{\rEng}What did I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.37,0:57:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以为下面会好一些\N{\rEng}I thought it would be nicer down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.46,0:57:34.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没传达太多信息\N{\rEng}You don't transmit too much information.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.96,0:57:35.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.46,0:57:39.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说 你没传达太多信息\N{\rEng}I said, you don't transmit too much information.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.63,0:57:41.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\rEng}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.55,0:57:45.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你夏天要干什么\N{\rEng}What are you doing over the summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.72,0:57:50.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在加油站找了份工作\N{\rEng}I have a job pumping gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.39,0:57:53.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你终于让最高法院听你的了 嗯\N{\rEng}You finally got the Supreme Court to hear your case, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.23,0:57:57.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你呢\N{\rEng}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.07,0:58:00.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.90,0:58:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得在这更好\N{\rEng}You thought it'd be nicer over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.07,0:58:08.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.42,0:58:18.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在干什么\N{\rEng}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.92,0:58:24.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找点什么送我妈妈生日礼物\N{\rEng}I'm looking for something for my mom's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.01,0:58:28.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的意思是说 万一有人偶尔在沙滩上丢了\N{\rEng}You mean, in case somebody happened to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.60,0:58:30.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个Cuisinart（美国厨具品牌）的东西或者一个钻石戒指\N{\rEng}a Cuisinart or a diamond ring lying on the beach?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.76,0:58:33.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 那就行 必须得是你做的 或者是你找到的东西\N{\rEng}Yeah, that would qualify. It has to be omething either you make or find.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.02,0:58:36.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 她生日是什么时候  - 下周\N{\rEng}- When's her birthday? - Next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.54,0:59:00.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真美\N{\rEng}That's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.21,0:59:03.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给你妈妈的\N{\rEng}It's for your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.55,0:59:08.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你送给她\N{\rEng}You give it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.72,0:59:11.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.81,0:59:17.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那一定更好\N{\rEng}It must be nicer over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.65,0:59:21.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过来 切这些\N{\rEng}Here, chop these.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.57,0:59:34.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不对 不对 不对 看 你到一边去\N{\rEng}No, no, no. Watch. Move.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.24,0:59:37.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拿着刀\N{\rEng}You hold the knife
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.08,0:59:39.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就这么做\N{\rEng}and you just do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.58,0:59:41.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很干净 我试试\N{\rEng}That's neat. Let me try.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.08,0:59:45.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 不 我是个素食者 我可不想你把你的小手指头切到菜里去\N{\rEng}No, no. I'm a vegetarian. I don't want pieces of tiny little fingers in my stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.67,0:59:47.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这 你来搅拌\N{\rEng}Here. You stir.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.51,0:59:51.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在等谁吗\N{\rEng}Were you expecting someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.94,1:00:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.52,1:00:03.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是罗娜\N{\rEng}I'm Lorna.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.11,1:00:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦克邀请了我\N{\rEng}Michael invited me.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.11,1:00:09.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 进来吧\N{\rEng}Well, come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.87,1:00:17.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你朋友在这\N{\rEng}Your friend's here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.87,1:00:19.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.96,1:00:24.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 嗨  - 我可以帮忙么\N{\rEng}- Hi. - Can I help?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.13,1:00:27.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不用 不用 没关系 谢谢\N{\rEng}No. No, it's okay. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.96,1:00:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你切到手指了\N{\rEng}You cut your finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.55,1:00:30.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.05,1:00:32.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是你女朋友\N{\rEng}Is this your girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.22,1:00:35.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 我是史蒂芬\N{\rEng}Hi, I'm Stephen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.06,1:00:41.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真好吃 宝贝 完全超出你的水平\N{\rEng}That was delicious, babe.You outdid yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.14,1:00:44.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为我自己的安格鲁-撒克逊教徒准备的朝圣食物\N{\rEng}This pilgrim food for my very own WASP.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.06,1:00:46.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是你得原谅我 亲爱的\N{\rEng}But you must forgive me, my darling.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.90,1:00:49.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没法做出这种果冻模具\N{\rEng}I couldn't get myself to make one of those Jell-O molds.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.15,1:00:52.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这次就原谅你了\N{\rEng}You're forgiven this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.99,1:00:55.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 （法语）\N{\rEng}And now, for the pie de ristance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.74,1:00:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我来 爸爸 - 你被逮捕了\N{\rEng}- Let me, Dad. - You're under arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.67,1:01:10.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看 你弄得肚脐那到处都是\N{\rEng}Look at this.You got it all over your bellybutton.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.01,1:01:12.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看\N{\rEng}Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.09,1:01:16.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦天哪 我老得都能把这房子弄着火\N{\rEng}Oh, God. I'm old enough to set the house on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.03,1:01:42.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 我以为你妈妈叫辛西娅\N{\rEng}I'm sorry, I thought your mother's name was Cynthia.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.29,1:01:45.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过生日的时候我们都叫山姆\N{\rEng}On birthdays, we're all Sam.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.62,1:01:47.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们家小小的传统\N{\rEng}It's a little family tradition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.13,1:01:50.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为我1968年那次超棒的用迷幻剂的经历\N{\rEng}resulting from a particularly good LSD trip I took in 1968.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.30,1:01:55.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再来点酒\N{\rEng}More wine?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.14,1:01:59.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你能让我歇会么  - 在欧洲 小孩子就能喝酒\N{\rEng}- Would you give me a break? - In Europe, kids drink wine.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.05,1:02:04.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我给"匿名酗酒者（美国一家帮助戒酒的机构）"打电话（指喝醉）之前 把给你妈妈的礼物拿来\N{\rEng}Get your mother her present before I call Alcoholics Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.73,1:02:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.41,1:02:23.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是我想要的\N{\rEng}It's just what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.41,1:02:25.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 真的  - 千真万确\N{\rEng}- Really? - Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.08,1:02:31.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是什么 蝴蝶\N{\rEng}What is that, a butterfly?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.00,1:02:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是 是个鲸鱼 当做礼物了\N{\rEng}No, it's a whale of a present.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.76,1:02:43.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢谢 - 我会弹奏它的\N{\rEng}- Thanks.- I'll play it for you sometime.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.52,1:02:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是罗娜的礼物\N{\rEng}This is from Lorna.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.86,1:02:56.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真美\N{\rEng}That's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.44,1:02:59.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你 罗娜\N{\rEng}Thank you, Lorna.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.03,1:03:04.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的礼物 等会给你\N{\rEng}Mine, you get later.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.70,1:03:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你保证\N{\rEng}You bet.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.87,1:03:08.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\rEng}On your feet!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.46,1:03:09.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我来帮忙\N{\rEng}Let me help.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.04,1:03:13.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢她\N{\rEng}I like her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.63,1:03:14.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.80,1:03:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我也喜欢她  - 我知道\N{\rEng}- I like her, too.- I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.77,1:04:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你确定这是菲利普斯家的孩子\N{\rEng}You sure this is the Phillips' kid?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.36,1:04:17.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在医院没被掉包吧 嗯\N{\rEng}They didn't switch you at the hospital or anything, did they?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.25,1:05:19.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我不敢想象他们有多不可理喻\N{\rEng}You know, I can't believe how incredible they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.67,1:05:24.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道如果我给我妈妈一个贝壳当做生日礼物 她会怎么做\N{\rEng}Do you know what my mother would do if I gave her a shell for her birthday?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.26,1:05:26.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没关系吧\N{\rEng}They're okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.84,1:05:30.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是你 害怕承认自己\N{\rEng}That's you all over afraid to commit yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.60,1:05:33.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以为这就是我\N{\rEng}I thought it was just me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.69,1:05:39.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和你在一起我很开心\N{\rEng}I'm very happy with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.11,1:05:44.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我也是\N{\rEng}I'm very happy with you, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.58,1:06:44.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没关系 我想这样\N{\rEng}It's okay, I want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.97,1:07:39.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你没去上厨艺课 - 你注意到了\N{\rEng}- You weren't in cooking. - You noticed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.97,1:07:41.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你去哪了  - 我翘课了\N{\rEng}- Where were you?- I cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.65,1:07:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 为什么  - 我不想见你\N{\rEng}- Why?- I didn't want to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.84,1:08:11.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德 我能和你说几句话么\N{\rEng}Manfield, could I talk to you for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.84,1:08:19.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没必要这么紧张 就算你做了错事\N{\rEng}You don't have to look so anxious.If you've done something wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.60,1:08:22.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道 我只是想知道你对大学的计划\N{\rEng}I don't know about it. I just want to talk to you about your college plans.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.77,1:08:26.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想休息一年 也许去欧洲旅行 听听音乐\N{\rEng}I was thinking of taking a year off, maybe traveling to Europe, listening to music.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.85,1:08:30.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能要求你做什么 但是我觉得你应该申请大学\N{\rEng}I can't tell you what to do, but I think you ought to make an application, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.44,1:08:32.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以推迟入学的\N{\rEng}You can always postpone entry.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.44,1:08:34.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想让你考虑考虑申请朱利亚德（纽约一所艺术学院）\N{\rEng}I'd like you to consider applying to Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.95,1:08:36.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提前录取\N{\rEng}Early admission.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.28,1:08:44.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我看了你成绩的档案 被录取应该没问题\N{\rEng}I looked at your academic records.You should have no trouble getting in.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.62,1:08:45.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 剩下的呢\N{\rEng}Where's the rest of it, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.87,1:08:47.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的档案里没有原先的学校的\N{\rEng}There's nothing in your file from your old school.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.63,1:08:51.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们搬家的时候弄丢了\N{\rEng}It was lost when we moved.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.13,1:08:54.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找回来的时候 我想看看\N{\rEng}When it comes through, I'd like to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.88,1:08:57.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时 你看看这个\N{\rEng}In the meantime, you look at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.97,1:09:05.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我会乐意给你写推荐信的\N{\rEng}I'd be happy to write you a letter of recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.81,1:09:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.15,1:09:12.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看完之后还给我\N{\rEng}Get back to me when you've looked at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.13,1:10:20.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不和我说话\N{\rEng}You wouldn't talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.64,1:10:23.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 起床\N{\rEng}Now, get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.30,1:10:26.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下楼 从后门出去\N{\rEng}Go down the stairs and out the back door.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.31,1:10:28.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,悄悄的\N{\rEng}Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.65,1:10:40.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就在你后面\N{\rEng}I'll be right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.25,1:10:54.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我光着脚呢\N{\rEng}I'm barefoot.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.37,1:11:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坐下\N{\rEng}Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.54,1:11:39.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在干嘛\N{\rEng}What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.88,1:11:44.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就是想和你说话\N{\rEng}I just wanted to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.22,1:11:49.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你那天在学校不听我讲\N{\rEng}You wouldn't listen, the other day at school.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.73,1:12:00.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我那天晚上没和你在一起 不是因为我不想\N{\rEng}I couldn't stay with you that night. Not because I didn't want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.08,1:12:12.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想回去 对我来说没什么\N{\rEng}If you want to go back, it's fine with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.33,1:12:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你是个笨蛋  - 不\N{\rEng}- You're a bully.- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.09,1:12:21.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说了谎\N{\rEng}I'm a liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.13,1:12:26.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我真名不是麦克\N{\rEng}My name isn't Michael.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.26,1:12:30.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是丹尼\N{\rEng}It's Danny.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.89,1:12:35.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我父母是阿瑟和安妮·波普\N{\rEng}My parents are Arthur and Annie Pope.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.02,1:12:42.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1971年他们因为让汽油弹实验室爆炸 和联邦调查局惹上了麻烦\N{\rEng}They're in trouble with the FBl for blowing up a napalm lab in 1971.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.44,1:12:44.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一个人差点就死了\N{\rEng}There was a man who was almost killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.40,1:12:46.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是个看门人 当时不该在那的\N{\rEng}A janitor abcwho wasn't supposed to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.45,1:12:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在所有生日蛋糕上都写"山姆"\N{\rEng}We put "Sam" on the birthday cakes, on all the birthday cakes
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.20,1:12:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为每到一个地方 我们就换新名字\N{\rEng}because we change our names every time we move.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.62,1:12:58.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从我两岁起 就一直这样了\N{\rEng}I've been doing this since I was two.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.88,1:13:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道别的办法\N{\rEng}I don't know any other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.38,1:13:05.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想告诉你我很抱歉\N{\rEng}I just wanted to tell you that I was sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.80,1:13:12.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想解释我为什么说不了太多事\N{\rEng}I wanted to explain why I can't talk about a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.72,1:13:16.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如大学 我不能去上大学 我不能离开他们\N{\rEng}Like college. I can't go to college.I can't leave them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.06,1:13:21.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我还想告诉你\N{\rEng}And I wanted to tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.02,1:13:24.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我为什么不能和你在一起\N{\rEng}why I couldn't be with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.73,1:13:28.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不能让你不知道 我不想对你说谎\N{\rEng}Not without your knowing.I didn't want to lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.57,1:13:34.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我没权利和你说这些的\N{\rEng}Now, I have no right in telling this to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.41,1:13:37.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对你 对他们 都很危险\N{\rEng}It's dangerous for you and it's dangerous for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.41,1:13:41.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起 我只是控制不住自己\N{\rEng}I'm sorry. I just couldn't stop myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.08,1:13:45.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想做什么都可以做 你可以告诉你爸爸 我不介意\N{\rEng}You can do what you want to. You can tell your dad anything. I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.67,1:13:48.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想要你知道\N{\rEng}I just needed you to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.18,1:13:52.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道我在做什么\N{\rEng}I don't know what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.35,1:13:56.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你\N{\rEng}And I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.19,1:14:02.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你\N{\rEng}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.39,1:14:35.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我要叫你什么\N{\rEng}What do I call you?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.97,1:14:38.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦克 什么都不用变\N{\rEng}Michael. Nothing changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.89,1:14:42.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们真的不想让你上大学么\N{\rEng}They really don't want you to go to school, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.85,1:14:46.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还没有谈\N{\rEng}We haven't talked about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.48,1:14:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不能问他们 - 为什么不\N{\rEng}- I can't ask them.- Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.82,1:14:53.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就意味着拆散整个家庭 我再也见不到他们\N{\rEng}It would mean breaking up the family not seeing them again.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.99,1:14:56.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们除了我们 什么都没有\N{\rEng}They don't have anything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.41,1:15:03.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能相信他们会要求你耗费自己的生命去陪着他们\N{\rEng}I can't believe that they'd want you to give up your whole life to stay with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.00,1:15:06.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和他们谈 他们会理解的\N{\rEng}Talk to them. They'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.96,1:15:13.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你有很多秘密 不是么\N{\rEng}You have a lot of secrets, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.93,1:15:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在你又多了一个\N{\rEng}Now you have another one.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.34,1:15:59.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去和罗娜约会了\N{\rEng}Been to see Lorna?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.90,1:16:11.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢她\N{\rEng}I like that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.90,1:16:13.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她很活泼\N{\rEng}She's full of beans.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.24,1:16:18.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你真心喜欢她 不是么\N{\rEng}You really like her, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.41,1:16:21.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,聪明的人总是最好的\N{\rEng}The smart ones are always the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.91,1:16:25.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和她睡了么\N{\rEng}Are you sleeping with her?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.33,1:16:29.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 嗯  - 好\N{\rEng}- Yeah. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.08,1:16:33.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,快去 睡觉去 明天还要上学\N{\rEng}Go ahead, hit the sack.You got school tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.20,1:17:45.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在停止专业钢琴之后\N{\rEng}How long have you been playing violin
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.57,1:17:48.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,演奏了多久小提琴\N{\rEng}after you stopped playing seriously piano?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.41,1:17:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大概五年\N{\rEng}About five years.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.75,1:17:52.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么时候来美国的\N{\rEng}When did you come to the States?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.42,1:17:54.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1980年\N{\rEng}In 1980.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.75,1:17:56.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 非常感谢\N{\rEng}All right. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.42,1:18:00.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德先生 我们准备好面试你了\N{\rEng}Mr. Manfield. We're ready for you now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.91,1:20:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你说你和谁学的\N{\rEng}Who did you say you studied with?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.99,1:20:37.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爱德华·菲利普斯\N{\rEng}Edward Phillips.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.66,1:20:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 在哪  - 沃特福德\N{\rEng}- Where was this?- Waterford.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.75,1:20:42.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 新泽西  - 对\N{\rEng}- New Jersey?- That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.25,1:20:45.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们好像没有你的学校档案\N{\rEng}We seem not to have all your school records.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.42,1:20:51.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以前的学校有 但是丢了\N{\rEng}There was a school fire at my old school, and the records were lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.68,1:20:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今年我们刚搬到新泽西\N{\rEng}We only moved to New Jersey this year.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.60,1:20:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你和菲利普斯先生只学了很短时间\N{\rEng}So you've only studied with Mr. Phillipsfor a short time.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.52,1:21:00.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是的 太太\N{\rEng}Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.94,1:21:02.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还和谁学过\N{\rEng}Who else have you worked with?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.11,1:21:07.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多不同的 但没有一个这么重要\N{\rEng}A lot of different people.No one important.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.19,1:21:10.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们经常搬家\N{\rEng}We move a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.44,1:21:13.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须给我们你的SAT成绩 还有\N{\rEng}You'll have to supply us with SAT scores and
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.82,1:21:16.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们必须要那些档案\N{\rEng}we'll have to have those records.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.21,1:21:22.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曼菲尔德先生\N{\rEng}Mr. Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.12,1:21:24.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哦 对不起\N{\rEng}Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.13,1:21:29.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你很有才华 你知道\N{\rEng}You are very talented, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.22,1:21:33.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 太太\N{\rEng}Thank you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.45,1:22:42.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给帕特森太太的芝士比萨\N{\rEng}A cheese pizza for Mrs. Patterson.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.29,1:22:45.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帕特森太太没订比萨\N{\rEng}I don't think Mrs. Patterson ordered a pizza.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.46,1:22:51.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是莫里山68434号么?\N{\rEng}Is this Murray Hill 68434?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.63,1:22:53.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是 - 那有人定了比萨\N{\rEng}- Yes.- Someone ordered it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.13,1:22:55.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}稍等
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.56,1:23:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}这比萨是怎么回事
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.31,1:23:12.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你订了一个\N{\rEng}You ordered one.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.65,1:23:14.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没有\N{\rEng}I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.07,1:23:18.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那你得付钱么\N{\rEng}Will you have to pay for it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.16,1:23:22.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 我得吃\N{\rEng}No, I'll have to eat it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.00,1:23:37.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我真的不在乎 等等 你下次不能敲门么\N{\rEng}I really don't care. Hold on.Could you knock next time?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.42,1:23:39.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 对不起  - 听着 我得走了 嗯 拜拜\N{\rEng}- I'm sorry.- Listen, I have to go. Yeah. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.39,1:23:45.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在想麦克有没有和你提到\N{\rEng}I was wondering if Michael had ever mentioned anything to you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.97,1:23:46.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他以前的学校\N{\rEng}about his old school.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.35,1:23:48.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不多 怎么问这个\N{\rEng}Not much. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.60,1:23:50.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都没把他的档案寄来\N{\rEng}They never sent his records.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.60,1:23:52.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢\N{\rEng}So?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.02,1:23:54.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我打电话给学校 说没有他的档案\N{\rEng}I called the school.They have no record of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.94,1:23:58.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有可能是电脑删掉了 或者什么的\N{\rEng}They probably got eaten by a computer or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.99,1:24:01.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在肯塔基州的蓝山 没有电脑的\N{\rEng}They don't have a computer in Blue Hill, Kentucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.20,1:24:05.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你研究他做什么\N{\rEng}What are you on his case for?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.20,1:24:09.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们对他一无所知  - 嗯 他以前是个杀人犯\N{\rEng}- We know nothing about him.- So, he's an axe murderer.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.71,1:24:13.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说 拜托 我以为他是你教过的音乐最好的学生\N{\rEng}I mean, come on! I thought he was the best music student you ever had.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.88,1:24:16.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是 但这解释不了他档案丢失的问题\N{\rEng}He is, but that doesn't explain his missing records.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.05,1:24:20.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想知道他究竟是谁 为什么不直接找他谈\N{\rEng}If you want to know who he is, why don't you talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.51,1:24:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是个人\N{\rEng}He's a person!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.97,1:24:27.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他不是电脑里的数据\N{\rEng}He's not a computer printout!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.02,1:24:36.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能不能把门关上\N{\rEng}Would you please close the door?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.57,1:24:45.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 曼菲尔德太太  - 是\N{\rEng}- Mrs. Manfield?- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.82,1:24:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢谢你能来 - 您好\N{\rEng}- Thank you for coming.- How do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.66,1:24:49.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 要不要来点咖啡  - 不 谢谢\N{\rEng}- Would you like some coffee?- No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.00,1:24:56.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想和您聊聊麦克\N{\rEng}I want to talk to you about Michael.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.34,1:25:00.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不想在学校见 这样他就不知道我们谈过\N{\rEng}I didn't want to meet at school because he doesn't know we're talking.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.55,1:25:02.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是他最近很失落也很紧张\N{\rEng}But he's been upset lately, and nervous.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.51,1:25:04.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我以为可能是家里出了点事\N{\rEng}I thought maybe there was something at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.18,1:25:07.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.10,1:25:12.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这是私人事情 我只是觉得如果我知道的话 我能帮得上忙\N{\rEng}I know these things are private. I just thought maybe I could help, if I knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.56,1:25:14.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是真的什么事都没有\N{\rEng}But there isn't anything. Really.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.85,1:25:17.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许他担心朱利亚德\N{\rEng}Maybe he's worried about Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.61,1:25:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朱利亚德\N{\rEng}Juilliard?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.78,1:25:23.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,您知道他的计划\N{\rEng}You know about his plans?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.03,1:25:26.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 是啊 当然 - 您不反对\N{\rEng}- Yeah, sure.- And you don't object?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.16,1:25:28.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不反对\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.20,1:25:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们对他的面试印象深刻\N{\rEng}They were very impressed with his audition.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.62,1:25:36.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们打算一拿到他的档案就录取他\N{\rEng}They're prepared to take him, just as soon as they get his records.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.88,1:25:42.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那时候他就得去了 是不是\N{\rEng}He'll have to go then, won't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.13,1:25:45.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是不是经济困难\N{\rEng}Is there a financial problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.05,1:25:48.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可不像洛克菲勒家族那么有钱\N{\rEng}We're not the Rockefellers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.97,1:25:50.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他可能会担心钱的问题\N{\rEng}He could be worried about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.97,1:25:52.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还过得下去\N{\rEng}We always manage.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.81,1:25:55.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有奖学金的 他可以拿\N{\rEng}There are scholarships. He could get one.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.64,1:25:57.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他很有才华\N{\rEng}He's very talented.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.48,1:26:00.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们也许不富裕 但我们关心孩子\N{\rEng}We may not have a lot, but we care about our kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.73,1:26:02.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我当然知道您关心\N{\rEng}I'm sure you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.90,1:26:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想知道他有过专业的老师么\N{\rEng}I was just wondering has he ever had a serious teacher?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.78,1:26:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是怎样达到这个水平的\N{\rEng}How has he gotten this far?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.87,1:26:11.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.45,1:26:15.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他在这学一点 那学一点 我们经常搬家 为什么问这个\N{\rEng}He's picked up a little here and there.We move around a lot. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.16,1:26:18.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我给蓝山打了电话 没有麦克·曼菲尔德的档案\N{\rEng}I called Blue Hill and they have no record of Michael Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.46,1:26:25.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是因为他在那注册的时候没有用曼菲尔德这个名字\N{\rEng}That's because he wasn't registered there under Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.17,1:26:28.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你看 我以前结过婚 保罗收养了他\N{\rEng}See, I was married before and Paul adopted him.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.59,1:26:31.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是直到今年才能合法地跟他的姓\N{\rEng}But it took until just this year to adopt his name legally.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.60,1:26:34.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在蓝山 他跟的是我前夫的姓\N{\rEng}He's under my old husband's name at Blue Hill.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.27,1:26:37.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有这些档案 他不能完成申请\N{\rEng}He can't finish his application without those records.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.77,1:26:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我会拿到的\N{\rEng}I'll get them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.35,1:26:42.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你必须得拿 因为他们只把档案给家长\N{\rEng}You'll have to, because they won't release them to anyone but a parent-
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.36,1:26:44.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说了 我会拿到的 行了么\N{\rEng}I said, I'll get them. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.94,1:26:48.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 现在 我得走了 - 好的 当然\N{\rEng}- Now, if you'll excuse me. - Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.24,1:29:00.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了 妈妈\N{\rEng}What's wrong, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.66,1:29:03.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没什么\N{\rEng}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.00,1:29:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你\N{\rEng}I just love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.52,1:29:28.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要去接你爸爸\N{\rEng}I've got to pick up your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.08,1:29:44.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喜欢么 我把货车卖了 买了这个 我觉得这样更实际一点\N{\rEng}Do you like it? I traded the van in for it.Thought it'd be more practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.46,1:29:47.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且 这让他们一直猜测\N{\rEng}Besides, it keeps them guessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.97,1:29:59.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了 山姆\N{\rEng}What's up, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.64,1:30:01.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别那么叫我\N{\rEng}Don't call me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.43,1:30:03.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.19,1:30:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,丹尼去申请大学了\N{\rEng}Danny's applied to college.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.65,1:30:13.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在哪\N{\rEng}Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.98,1:30:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,朱利亚德\N{\rEng}Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.44,1:30:17.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么知道的\N{\rEng}How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.65,1:30:20.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,菲利普斯 他想让他去\N{\rEng}Phillips. He wants him to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.66,1:30:25.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他为什么不离咱们家的事远点\N{\rEng}Why doesn't he keep his goddamn nose out of our business?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.58,1:30:27.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为他觉得他很有才华\N{\rEng}Because he thinks he's talented.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.08,1:30:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,丹尼告诉你这些了么\N{\rEng}Has Danny told you about any of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.92,1:30:32.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.34,1:30:38.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们要怎么做\N{\rEng}What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.43,1:30:40.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,妈的\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.47,1:30:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去他妈的\N{\rEng}Goddamn fucking shit!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.93,1:30:46.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他为什么不能去上大学\N{\rEng}Why can't he go?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.60,1:30:48.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为如果他去了 我们就再也见不到他了\N{\rEng}Because we'll never see him again if he does.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.60,1:30:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不能 我们可以安排和他见面\N{\rEng}Why? We could arrange to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.77,1:30:53.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想这样\N{\rEng}Is that what you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.19,1:30:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在机场休息室见十分钟 然后联邦调查局一辈子跟在他屁股后面\N{\rEng}Ten minutes at an airport lounge, and the FBl all over his ass the rest of the time?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.11,1:31:02.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想让他像我父母一样站在电话亭 洗衣房\N{\rEng}You want him standing in phone booths and Laundromats like my parents
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.70,1:31:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只能通过通信网络和我们联系 我不想这样\N{\rEng}only connecting with us through the network? I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.95,1:31:09.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果他去了 我们就再也见不到他了\N{\rEng}If he goes we're never going to see him again
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.87,1:31:12.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能接受\N{\rEng}and that is unacceptable to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.13,1:31:25.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我连想都不会想\N{\rEng}I never even let myself think about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.39,1:31:28.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我真傻\N{\rEng}I was so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.39,1:31:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我只想让我们在一起\N{\rEng}All I wanted was that we would be together.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.07,1:31:39.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我应该把丹尼扔给我妈妈的\N{\rEng}We should have left Danny with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.49,1:31:43.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们都不该有哈利 - 闭嘴\N{\rEng}- We never should have had Harry.- Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.82,1:31:48.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能这样 阿瑟 看看我们对孩子都做了些什么\N{\rEng}I can't, Arthur.Look what we're doing to these kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.83,1:31:51.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们一辈子都像罪犯一样在逃亡\N{\rEng}They've been running their whole lives like criminals.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.25,1:31:52.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们什么都没做\N{\rEng}And they didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.91,1:31:54.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这不公平\N{\rEng}It isn't fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.17,1:31:56.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我知道这他妈的不公平\N{\rEng}I know it isn't goddamned fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.00,1:32:00.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们经过了一些冲击 但是你这样逼自己于事无补\N{\rEng}They've taken some bumps, but it's not going to help anything to beat yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.01,1:32:05.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看他们 看在上帝的份上\N{\rEng}Look at them, for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.09,1:32:07.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看这些孩子 他们多么优秀\N{\rEng}Look at those kids. They're magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.60,1:32:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们很美\N{\rEng}They're beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.18,1:32:12.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很聪明很体贴\N{\rEng}And bright. Caring.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.44,1:32:15.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能做得多坏呢\N{\rEng}How badly could we have done?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.02,1:32:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该自首\N{\rEng}We should turn ourselves in.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.69,1:32:25.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后接下来15年都呆在监狱里\N{\rEng}So we can sit in prison for the next 15 years
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.36,1:32:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从铁窗里看我们的孩子们\N{\rEng}and look at the kids through bars?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.20,1:32:31.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每次还只能看一个小时\N{\rEng}You can only get through this one day, one hour at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.95,1:32:34.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我就准备这么做\N{\rEng}That's what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.71,1:32:38.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,丹尼已经长大了\N{\rEng}And Danny's all grown up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.30,1:32:43.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们该放他走了\N{\rEng}We have to let him go.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.64,1:32:55.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗牙疼死我了\N{\rEng}This tooth is killing me.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.64,1:32:58.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得补的东西掉了 该去看看乔纳\N{\rEng}I think I lost a filling. Better go see Jonah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.31,1:33:01.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我会坐公交车\N{\rEng}I'll take a bus.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.40,1:33:04.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你去市内的时候我总是担心 - 为什么\N{\rEng}- I always worry when you go into the city.- Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.07,1:33:07.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为在那他们谁都能看见\N{\rEng}Because that's where they get everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.32,1:33:08.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很安静\N{\rEng}It's been quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.16,1:33:12.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候太安静了\N{\rEng}Sometimes it gets too quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.58,1:33:14.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还记得孩子小时候你常说的话么\N{\rEng}Remember what you used to say when the kids were small?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.00,1:33:17.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"别着急 除非你什么都听不见了 "\N{\rEng}"Don't worry unless you don't hear anything. "
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.17,1:33:19.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小心点 好不好\N{\rEng}Be careful, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.51,1:33:33.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我什么都没看见 X光片里也什么都没有\N{\rEng}I don't see anything. And there's nothing on the x-ray.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.51,1:33:35.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没在抱怨\N{\rEng}I'm not complaining.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.85,1:33:39.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还需要什么吗\N{\rEng}You need anything else?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.36,1:33:45.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 谢谢 我们很好 我在为一个全科医生工作\N{\rEng}No, thanks. We're okay. I'm working for a GP.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.86,1:33:47.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现金可以吗\N{\rEng}How about cash?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.45,1:33:49.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以\N{\rEng}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.37,1:33:55.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你提前告诉我 我可以安排更多的\N{\rEng}If you'd give me some notice, I could arrange to have more.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.62,1:33:58.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 很好了 谢谢\N{\rEng}No. This is great. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.96,1:34:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你总是让我觉得这么愧疚  - 为什么\N{\rEng}- You always make me feel so guilty. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.21,1:34:04.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是你的生活方式\N{\rEng}You're living it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.30,1:34:07.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是啊 我猜我是\N{\rEng}Yeah, I guess I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.97,1:34:13.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔纳 我需要你帮我打个电话\N{\rEng}Jonah, I need youabcto make a phone call for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.72,1:34:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然可以\N{\rEng}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.40,1:34:25.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夫人\N{\rEng}Madame?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.01,1:34:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 爸爸\N{\rEng}Hi, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.01,1:35:00.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我让乔纳做的这个\N{\rEng}I asked Jonah to set this up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.36,1:35:07.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想 可以叫警察\N{\rEng}You can call the cops if you want to.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.95,1:35:17.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起\N{\rEng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.87,1:35:21.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对我也很难\N{\rEng}This is hard for me, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.12,1:35:26.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 夫人要点什么饮料  - 不 谢谢\N{\rEng}- Will madame have a drink?- No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.97,1:35:36.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想知道14年不见你的孩子\N{\rEng}I wonder if you'll ever know what it's like
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.97,1:35:39.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是什么感觉\N{\rEng}not to see your child for 14 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.06,1:35:45.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,连他是死是活都不知道\N{\rEng}Not knowing whether she's living or dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.24,1:35:54.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道这孩子是不是\N{\rEng}Not knowing whether that child
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.49,1:35:59.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要对别人的死亡或者伤残负责\N{\rEng}is responsible for the death and mutilation of other human beings.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.83,1:36:04.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要不要让你自己\N{\rEng}Whether to hold yourself responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.83,1:36:06.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为那死亡或伤残负责任\N{\rEng}for that death and mutilation
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.17,1:36:11.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为扣动扳机 引爆炸弹的是你的孩子\N{\rEng}because it is your child who is pulling the triggers, setting the bombs.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.17,1:36:13.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我没杀任何人\N{\rEng}I didn't kill anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.84,1:36:19.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不是来为自己辩护或是谈政治的\N{\rEng}I didn't come here to defend myself or to talk politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.68,1:36:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不相信我当时那么做是出于良心要结束战争\N{\rEng}If you don't believe by now that what I did was an act of conscience to stop the war
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.85,1:36:28.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我说什么你都不会明白\N{\rEng}then there's nothing I can say to you that's going to make you understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.02,1:36:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个人失明 还残疾了\N{\rEng}A man was blinded and paralyzed.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.11,1:36:32.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他本不该在那的\N{\rEng}He wasn't supposed to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.36,1:36:38.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不觉得 有些时候\N{\rEng}Don't you think there have been times
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.95,1:36:41.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我宁愿让自己失明 让自己残疾 来挽回这一切么\N{\rEng}that I would have blinded and paralyzed myself to take that back?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.12,1:36:43.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那都是阿瑟的影响\N{\rEng}It's all Arthur's influence.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.79,1:36:45.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 爸爸 不是\N{\rEng}No, Dad, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.37,1:36:47.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是我的主意\N{\rEng}It was my idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.29,1:36:50.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我活在我自己的选择带来的后果中\N{\rEng}I'm living with the consequences of my own choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.88,1:36:52.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我不信  - 那是你的问题\N{\rEng}- I don't believe it.- Well, that's your problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.88,1:36:54.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈和我\N{\rEng}Your mother and me
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.71,1:36:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你为我们考虑过么\N{\rEng}Do you think about us?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.14,1:37:06.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你非得这么问么 - 对\N{\rEng}- Do you really have to ask that?- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.40,1:37:14.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上一次我记得你对我说\N{\rEng}The last thing I remember you saying to me
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.32,1:37:18.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我是个帝国主义的蠢猪\N{\rEng}was that I was an imperialist pig
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.99,1:37:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个人为了战争 贫穷和种族主义承担责任\N{\rEng}personally responsible for the war, the spread of poverty, racism.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.24,1:37:26.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我还年轻 - 是\N{\rEng}- I was young.- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.58,1:37:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还年轻\N{\rEng}You were young.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.92,1:37:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有才华\N{\rEng}And talented.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.26,1:37:38.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美丽\N{\rEng}And beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.68,1:37:41.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么充满了爱\N{\rEng}And so full of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.18,1:37:47.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上帝啊 安妮 你为什么把它们都抛弃了\N{\rEng}My God, Annie.Why did you throw it all away?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.86,1:37:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈很想你 还有丹尼\N{\rEng}Your mother misses you terribly. And Danny.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.70,1:38:03.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会收留他么 爸爸\N{\rEng}Will you take him, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.03,1:38:07.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他想学音乐\N{\rEng}He wants to study music.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.54,1:38:10.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他很好\N{\rEng}He's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.54,1:38:12.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们想让他去朱利亚德\N{\rEng}They want him at Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.38,1:38:16.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像他们当时想让你一样\N{\rEng}Just like they wanted you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.71,1:38:22.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你还有那个用来练习的板\N{\rEng}Do you still have that practice board?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.38,1:38:26.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一直到现在 丹尼就是在那上面学会弹琴\N{\rEng}So far. Danny learned to play piano on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.72,1:38:30.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你教他的\N{\rEng}So you taught him?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.98,1:38:36.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不觉得这有点讽刺么\N{\rEng}There's some irony in this, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.73,1:38:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你现在在这\N{\rEng}Here you are
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.90,1:38:43.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,求我把丹尼带到\N{\rEng}asking me to take Danny
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.07,1:38:48.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你曾经唯恐避之不及的人生里\N{\rEng}into a life that you ran from like a shot out of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.91,1:38:52.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他真的想要么\N{\rEng}Is this what he wants?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.66,1:38:54.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得是\N{\rEng}I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.58,1:38:57.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他没告诉我就自己去了面试\N{\rEng}He got himself an audition without telling me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.34,1:39:04.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他会需要钱和照顾他的人\N{\rEng}He'll need money, and people to care for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.26,1:39:07.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不觉得你要的太多了么\N{\rEng}Don't you think this is too much to ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.68,1:39:10.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我几乎不认识这男孩\N{\rEng}I hardly know the boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.60,1:39:14.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们收留了他\N{\rEng}If we take him
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.94,1:39:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我们去哪都会有联邦调查局的人跟着\N{\rEng}there'd be FBl agents following us everywhere we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.94,1:39:23.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就再也见不到他\N{\rEng}You'd never be able to see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.36,1:39:27.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们太老了 不能这么做了\N{\rEng}We're too old for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.87,1:39:32.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 我觉得我要的太多了\N{\rEng}Yeah, I think it's too much to ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.46,1:39:41.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我还有一个儿子\N{\rEng}I have another son.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.88,1:39:44.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他十岁 叫哈利\N{\rEng}He's 10. Harry.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.22,1:39:48.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在新闻上听说了\N{\rEng}I heard about it on the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.05,1:39:51.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我打算\N{\rEng}I plan to turn myself in
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.81,1:39:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在他再也不需要我的时候就去自首 在他足够大的时候\N{\rEng}when he doesn't need me anymore.When he's old enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.39,1:39:57.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿瑟呢\N{\rEng}And Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.23,1:39:59.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不能为他说话\N{\rEng}I can't speak for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.82,1:40:05.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请你考虑考虑\N{\rEng}Please think about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.58,1:40:14.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我该走了\N{\rEng}I should go.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.00,1:40:19.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安妮\N{\rEng}Annie.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.50,1:40:24.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他可以来我们家\N{\rEng}He can come to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.19,1:40:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请您告诉妈妈 我爱她\N{\rEng}Please, tell Mom that I love her.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.86,1:40:47.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我经常想你俩\N{\rEng}And I've thought about you both so often.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.45,1:40:50.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我把你叫出来\N{\rEng}I've called out to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.12,1:40:56.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对不起我给你们带来这么多痛苦\N{\rEng}I'm sorry that I've caused you so much pain.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.21,1:41:03.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我猜我要知道这是什么感觉了\N{\rEng}I guess I'm about to see what it feels like.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.30,1:41:10.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你 爸爸\N{\rEng}I love you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.84,1:41:48.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我去见了我父亲\N{\rEng}I saw my father.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.67,1:41:51.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你什么\N{\rEng}You what?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.34,1:41:54.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我见了唐纳德\N{\rEng}I saw Donald.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.35,1:41:59.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就那么走进他办公室坐在他桌边\N{\rEng}You just walked into his office and sat down at his desk?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.60,1:42:00.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.77,1:42:04.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我在"小锅"和他吃了午饭\N{\rEng}I had lunch with him at La Petite Marmite.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.52,1:42:06.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,干什么\N{\rEng}What for?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.86,1:42:09.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想看看他要不要收留丹尼.\N{\rEng}To see if he'd take Danny.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:10.69,1:42:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收留丹尼\N{\rEng}Take Danny?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.86,1:42:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样他就可以上大学了\N{\rEng}So he can go to college.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.70,1:42:17.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你开玩笑吧\N{\rEng}You're kidding.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.29,1:42:20.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他说他会的\N{\rEng}He said he would.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.62,1:42:23.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他说他会\N{\rEng}He said he would?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.46,1:42:26.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知不知道会发生什么\N{\rEng}You know what could have happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.71,1:42:30.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,菲利普斯要你这么做的\N{\rEng}Did Phillips put you up to this?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.96,1:42:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没人要求我这么做\N{\rEng}Nobody put me up to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.63,1:42:37.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和菲利普斯无关 这是为了丹尼\N{\rEng}It's not about Phillips. It's about Danny.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.97,1:42:41.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他想去 他申请了 去了面试\N{\rEng}He wants to go. He applied.He went to an audition.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.97,1:42:44.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他他妈的去哪了  - 朱利亚德\N{\rEng}- He went fucking where?- Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.40,1:42:49.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不相信我的耳朵\N{\rEng}I don't believe my ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.23,1:42:51.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就给他一次机会吧\N{\rEng}Just give him a chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.73,1:42:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我要给黛博拉打电话 看看她能不能假造些档案\N{\rEng}I'm going to call Deborah and see if she can make him up some records.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.90,1:42:56.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么\N{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.24,1:42:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为菲力普斯给我填在申请表上的学校打了电话\N{\rEng}Because Phillips called the school I put on the registration form
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.99,1:43:01.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后他们告诉他没有叫麦克·曼菲尔德的人\N{\rEng}and they told him there was no Michael Manfield.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.24,1:43:03.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会没事的\N{\rEng}It's going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.41,1:43:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他可以及时做好档案的 阿瑟\N{\rEng}He can get records made up in time. Artie!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.42,1:43:11.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们要搬了 孩子们\N{\rEng}We're moving base camp, kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.84,1:43:14.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再呆几天 我们就走\N{\rEng}We have a few days, and we're gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.17,1:43:16.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把踪迹都销毁掉\N{\rEng}Cover your tracks.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.18,1:43:18.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,听见没\N{\rEng}You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.01,1:43:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你有想告诉我的事么\N{\rEng}You have anything you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.35,1:43:23.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.52,1:43:24.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:43.29,1:43:45.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爸爸想要搬走\N{\rEng}My father wants to move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.29,1:43:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么\N{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.55,1:43:55.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他有眼见\N{\rEng}He gets a sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.97,1:43:59.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就那样\N{\rEng}Just like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.89,1:44:01.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就那样\N{\rEng}Just like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.89,1:44:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,什么时候\N{\rEng}When?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.14,1:44:08.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随时\N{\rEng}Anytime.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.31,1:44:11.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就那么消失了\N{\rEng}You'll just disappear?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.90,1:44:20.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那我们怎么办\N{\rEng}What about us?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.49,1:44:25.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们需要我  - 我需要你\N{\rEng}- They need me.- I need you!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.00,1:44:29.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没和他们谈\N{\rEng}You didn't talk to them?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.50,1:44:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不能一直逃离你没有责任的事\N{\rEng}You can't keep running from something you had nothing to do with.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.26,1:44:39.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你应该有你自己的机会\N{\rEng}You deserve your own chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.86,1:44:56.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我想和你谈谈 - 没什么可谈的\N{\rEng}- I want to talk to you.- There's nothing to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.36,1:44:57.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,菲利普斯知道的太多了\N{\rEng}Phillips knows too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.86,1:45:00.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在让你的情感影响你的判断\N{\rEng}You were letting your feelings affect your judgment.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.45,1:45:02.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且 这就是上学\N{\rEng}Besides, it's academic.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.79,1:45:16.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没人会说的\N{\rEng}Nobody will talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.79,1:45:17.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不知道\N{\rEng}You don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.21,1:45:21.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们能抓的都会抓\N{\rEng}They're going to try to pick up everyone they can now.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.14,1:45:25.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们在这的日子到头了\N{\rEng}We're finished here.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.73,1:45:36.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们可以慢慢收手的 不是么  - 我们必须走了\N{\rEng}- We can close up shop slowly, can't we?- We'll have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.56,1:45:39.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不然就会引起注意\N{\rEng}Otherwise we'll attract attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.15,1:45:42.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大家都去上班和上学 等接下来的通知\N{\rEng}Everybody goes to work and school until further notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.65,1:45:45.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有问题我们就在80号公路附近的野餐区见面\N{\rEng}If there's a problem will meet at the picnic area near Route 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.99,1:45:49.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还没有理由觉得他们在追捕我们 所以冷静\N{\rEng}There's no reason to think they're onto us yet, so stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:10.43,1:46:13.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 爸爸 我能和你说一会话么  - 现在不行\N{\rEng}- Dad, can I talk to you a minute?- Not now.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.02,1:46:21.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想留下\N{\rEng}I was thinking about staying.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.19,1:46:24.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 你不得去上课么  - 还有半个小时\N{\rEng}- Don't you have school?- In half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.13,1:46:43.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想留下\N{\rEng}I want to stay.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.63,1:46:45.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,留下\N{\rEng}Stay?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.80,1:46:49.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得现在是讨论这个问题的时候么\N{\rEng}Do you think this is a good time to discuss this?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:51.22,1:46:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在不能说 我们遇到麻烦了\N{\rEng}We can't talk now. We're in trouble here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.98,1:46:56.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你了\N{\rEng}I taught you!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.89,1:46:59.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你了 我们不能打破我们之间的联系\N{\rEng}I taught you! We cannot break rank.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.98,1:47:02.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个集体的能力是由它最弱的一环决定的\N{\rEng}A unit is only as good as its weakest link.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.32,1:47:03.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们是一个集体\N{\rEng}We're a unit!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.90,1:47:08.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些都是我教你的 不记得了么\N{\rEng}I taught you all of this don't you remember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.49,1:47:12.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不想听你\N{\rEng}I don't want to hear you talking about this
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.16,1:47:14.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在你妈妈或者你弟弟面前说这些 听见没有\N{\rEng}in front of your mother or your brother, do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.16,1:47:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我说 听见没有\N{\rEng}I said, do you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.91,1:47:19.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这回说完了没\N{\rEng}Are we finished talking about this now?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.59,1:47:28.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,泰勒女士\N{\rEng}Mrs. Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.26,1:47:32.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把所有东西都拿出来 穿上袍子就行\N{\rEng}Just remove everything and put on the gown.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.18,1:47:33.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几分钟内就可以见医生了\N{\rEng}The doctor will see you in a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.85,1:47:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好的 我马上就回来给你称体重\N{\rEng}All right. I'll be right back to weigh you.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.77,1:47:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能帮我拉拉链么 亲爱的\N{\rEng}Could you help me with this zipper, dear?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.36,1:47:46.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道昨晚伊利莎白·鲍威尔怎么了么\N{\rEng}Did you hear what happened to Elizabeth Powell last night?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.11,1:47:48.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道\N{\rEng}No, I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.53,1:47:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,联邦调查局找她了\N{\rEng}The FBl came to see her.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.53,1:47:53.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抢银行 还杀死了警察的那次\N{\rEng}The car that was used in that bank robbery
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.37,1:47:55.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们用的车\N{\rEng}where they killed those policemen
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.95,1:47:58.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是用她的信用卡租的\N{\rEng}it was rented with her credit card.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.12,1:48:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你相信么\N{\rEng}Can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.04,1:48:05.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们怎么能拿到她的卡 她自己都从来不用\N{\rEng}How could they have got hold of her card? She never even uses it herself.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.21,1:48:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是为什么她没注意到卡不见了\N{\rEng}That's how come she didn't notice it was gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.47,1:48:12.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些人是一帮恶棍 泰勒女士\N{\rEng}Those people are crooks, Mrs. Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.55,1:48:14.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们很有可能就是从通讯录里查出她的电话\N{\rEng}They probably just took her name out of the phone book
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.89,1:48:16.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后假造了一张卡\N{\rEng}and made up a false card.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.64,1:48:18.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能想象这多背运么\N{\rEng}Can you imagine the bad luck?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.90,1:48:31.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请找保罗·曼菲尔德先生 我是他妻子\N{\rEng}Paul Manfield, please. His wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.41,1:48:35.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们很着急\N{\rEng}We're in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.08,1:48:39.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,格斯从我一个病人那偷了信用卡 他用它来租车\N{\rEng}Gus took plastic from one of my patients.He used it to rent the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.92,1:48:53.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的 我要去抽根烟\N{\rEng}Frankie? I'm going out for a smoke.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.69,1:49:14.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们着急么 妈妈  - 嗯 我们得找到丹尼\N{\rEng}- Are we in a hurry, Mom?- Yeah. We have to get Danny.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.37,1:49:22.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,希望你丈夫还好\N{\rEng}I hope your husband is all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.55,1:49:31.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了 走吧\N{\rEng}Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.96,1:49:34.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 妈妈 我在那见你 - 我们时间不多\N{\rEng}- Mom, I'll meet you there.- We don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.81,1:49:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,塞林格在《麦田里的守望者》中用意象\N{\rEng}Salinger uses imagery in Catcher in the Rye to-
Dialogue: 0,1:49:44.89,1:49:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 抱歉  - 怎么\N{\rEng}- Excuse me.- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.14,1:49:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麦奎尔先生要见罗娜·菲利普斯\N{\rEng}Mr. McGuire would like to see Lorna Phillips.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.90,1:49:51.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他写假条了么  - 没有 女士\N{\rEng}- Did he send a note?- No, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.32,1:49:53.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,菲利普斯小姐\N{\rEng}Ms. Phillips?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.17,1:50:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们要走了\N{\rEng}We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.17,1:50:14.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你没和他们谈\N{\rEng}You didn't ask them?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.92,1:50:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我谈了\N{\rEng}I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.93,1:50:19.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿瑟崩溃了\N{\rEng}Artie fell apart.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.93,1:50:21.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他根本不讲理\N{\rEng}He didn't even make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.35,1:50:25.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有我们他活不下去\N{\rEng}Without us, he can't keep it going.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.85,1:50:28.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他需要我们支撑着他\N{\rEng}He needs us to hold him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.02,1:50:32.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有家庭都会拆散的\N{\rEng}All families break up.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.69,1:50:37.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么要把别人的人生当做自己的负担\N{\rEng}Why do you have to carry the burden of someone else's life?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.45,1:50:41.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他是我父亲\N{\rEng}He's my father.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.62,1:50:47.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你\N{\rEng}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.04,1:50:53.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我要离开了\N{\rEng}But I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.21,1:50:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道怎么道别\N{\rEng}I don't know how to say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:01.22,1:51:02.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就不要\N{\rEng}Well, don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.92,1:51:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- 他在哪  - 他会来这\N{\rEng}- Where is he? - He'll be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.00,1:51:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他去和她女朋友道别了\N{\rEng}He went to say goodbye to his girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.01,1:51:39.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他比这知道得多\N{\rEng}He knows better than this.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.26,1:51:47.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是鲍勃·斯通 带来Z-90新闻时间\N{\rEng}This is Bob Stone, with a Z-90 newsbreak.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.10,1:51:52.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新泽西警方昨天下午报告了\N{\rEng}New Jersey police have reported the death of Liberation Army member Gus Winant
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.44,1:51:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在抢劫银行后一直在逃的自由军成员格斯·维纳特的死亡\N{\rEng}at large after the bank robbery yesterday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.77,1:51:58.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他在沃特福德附近偷了辆车并试图逃逸\N{\rEng}He was shot resisting arrest near Waterford
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.19,1:52:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因拒捕而被枪击\N{\rEng}where he had stolen a car and was attempting to flee.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.11,1:52:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,五点带来更多 现在回到球赛\N{\rEng}More at 5:00.We return you now to the ball game.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.72,1:52:25.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把自行车从后面拿出来\N{\rEng}Get the bike out of the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.98,1:52:35.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,骑上\N{\rEng}Now get on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.32,1:52:39.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在说什么 爸爸\N{\rEng}What are you talking about, Dad-
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.65,1:52:43.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,骑上车 你现在靠自己了 孩子\N{\rEng}Get on the bike. You're on your own, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.57,1:52:48.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想让你去朱利亚德\N{\rEng}I want you to go to Juilliard.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.41,1:52:50.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是爸爸 我想和你走\N{\rEng}But, Dad, I want to go with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.58,1:52:55.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会再见的 你放心\N{\rEng}We'll see you again. You can be sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.83,1:53:01.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你妈妈和你外公都安排好了\N{\rEng}Your mother has arranged things with your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.25,1:53:02.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给他打电话\N{\rEng}Call him.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.01,1:53:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在这也有了些朋友了\N{\rEng}And I think you have some friends around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.09,1:53:07.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你 宝贝儿\N{\rEng}I love you, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.18,1:53:13.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们都爱你\N{\rEng}We all love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.35,1:53:16.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 去闯自己的人生吧\N{\rEng}Now, go out there and make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.11,1:53:19.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和我妈妈试过了\N{\rEng}Your mother and I tried.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.94,1:53:25.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不要让任何人怀疑你\N{\rEng}Don't let anyone tell you any different.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.13,1:53:43.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再见 丹尼\N{\rEng}Goodbye, Danny!


